descr: A vascular disease that is characterized by generalized calcification of the arterial internal elastic lamina, leading to rupture of the lamina and occlusive changes in the tunica intima with stenosis and decreased elasticity of the vessel wall.

name: arterial tortuosity syndrome
descr: A connective tissue disease that is characterized by elongation and generalized tortuosity of the major arteries including the aorta.

name: distal arthrogryposis
descr: A muscle tissue disease characterized by congenital joint contractures of hand and feet.

name: Arts syndrome
descr: An X-linked disease that is characterized by profound congenital sensorineural hearing impairment, early-onset hypotonia, delayed motor development, mild to moderate intellectual disability, ataxia, and increased risk of infection and has_material_basis_in mutations of the PRPS1 gene.

name: atelosteogenesis
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by specific patterns of aplasia/hypoplasia of humeri, femora, spine in newborns.

name: atransferrinemia
descr: A metal metabolism disorder that is characterized by transferrin deficiency, microcytic anemia, and iron loading, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the structural gene for transferrin on chromosome 3q22.

name: familial atrial fibrillation
descr: An atrial fibrillation that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of the familial atrial fibrillation (ATFB) genes.

name: atrioventricular septal defect
descr: A congenital heart septal defect characterized by an abnormal or inadequate fusion of the superior and inferior endocardial cushions with the mid portion of the atrial septum and the muscular portion of the ventricular septum, thus allowing extra blood to circulate the lungs.

name: Baller-Gerold syndrome
descr: A synostosis characterized by coronal craniosynostosis, short stature, and aplasia or hypoplasia of the radial bone.

name: Bamforth-Lazarus syndrome
descr: A hypothyroidism that is characterized by thyroid dysgenesis, cleft palate, spiky hair and bifid epiglottis, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the FKHL15 gene on chromosome 9q22.

name: pseudo-TORCH syndrome 1
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by congenital microcephaly, intracranial calcifications, severe developmental delay, severe developmental delay, simplified gyration and polymicrogyria.

name: Bannayan-Riley-Ruvalcaba syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by macrocephaly, multiple noncancerous tumors and hamartomas, and dark freckles on the penis, and has_material_basis_in heterozygous germline mutation in the PTEN gene on chromosome 10q23.

name: Bart-Pumphrey syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by leukonychia, wart-like skin growths, palmoplantar keratoderma and hearing loss, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the GJB2 gene on chromosome 13q12.

name: biotin-responsive basal ganglia disease
descr: A basal ganglia disease that is characterized by recurrent subacute encephalopathy, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom seizure, has_symptom ataxia, has_symptom dystonia, has_symptom supranuclear facial palsy, has_symptom external ophthalmoplegia, and has_symptom dysphagia.

name: Beare-Stevenson cutis gyrata syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by cutis gyrata, acanthosis nigricans and craniosynostosis, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the FGFR2 gene on chromosome 10q26.

name: vitelliform macular dystrophy
descr: A macular degeneration that it is characterized by the disruption of cells in a small area near the center of the retina, the macula and may cause progressive vision loss.

name: bestrophinopathy
descr: A macular degeneration that is characterized by central vision loss, an absent electrooculogram light rise and a reduced electroretinogram, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the BEST1 gene on chromosome 11q12.

name: Bethlem myopathy
descr: A congenital muscular dystrophy that is characterized by myopathy and joint contractures that progresses slowly, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of heterozygous mutation in the COL6A1 gene, the COL6A2 gene, or the COL6A3 gene.

name: Bietti crystalline corneoretinal dystrophy
descr: A retinal degeneration that is characterized by crystals in the cornea, shiny deposits on the retina and progressive atrophy of the retina, choriocapillaris and choroid, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the CYP4V2 gene on chromosome 4q35.

name: fetal alcohol syndrome
descr: A fetal alcohol spectrum disorder that results in severe mental and physical defects which can develop in a child when the mother drinks alcohol during pregnancy. The presenting features include craniofacial dysmorphology (microcephaly, smooth philtrum, thin upper lip, small eye openings), pre- and postnatal growth deficiency, and central nervous system dysfunction.

name: partial fetal alcohol syndrome
descr: A fetal alcohol spectrum disorder that results in most, but not all, of the growth deficiency and/or craniofacial features of fetal alcohol syndrome including central nervous system dysfunction due to prenatal alcohol exposure.

name: alcohol-related neurodevelopmental disorder
descr: A fetal alcohol spectrum disorder that results in central nervous system dysfunction and behavioral and/or cognitive deficits due to prenatal alcohol exposure.

name: alcohol-related birth defect
descr: A fetal alcohol spectrum disorder that results in damage to organs, bones, or muscles due to prenatal alcohol exposure.

name: spastic cerebral palsy
descr: A cerebral palsy that is caused by damage in the outer layer of the brain, the cerebral cortex, which results in increased tone, or tension, in a muscle causing abnormal movements.

name: ataxic cerebral palsy
descr: A cerebral palsy that is caused by damage to the cerebellum, which affects muscle coordination, particularly in the limb. Some individuals suffer from hypotonia, tremors, difficulty with visual and/or auditory processing.

name: female breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that develops from breast tissue in females.

name: dyskinetic cerebral palsy
descr: A cerebral palsy that is caused by damage to the extrapyramidal motor system and/or pyramidal tract and to the basal ganglia, which results in mixed muscle tone (hypertonia and hypotonia). The individuals have trouble holding themselves in an upright, steady position for sitting or walking, and often show involuntary motions.

name: mixed cerebral palsy
descr: A cerebral palsy that is caused by injury to both the pyramidal and extra pyramidal areas of the brain, which results in both the tight muscle tone and the involuntary movements. The individual have difficulty with speaking and swallowing.

name: congenital bile acid synthesis defect
descr: A steroid inherited metabolic disorder characterized by abnormal conversion of cholesterol into bile acids which occurs predominantly in the liver.

name: Birk-Barel syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by intellectual disability, hypotonia, hyperactivity and facies, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the KCNK9 gene on chromosome 8q24.

name: Birt-Hogg-Dube syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by the development of skin papules on the head, face and upper torso, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the gene encoding folliculin on chromosome 17p11.

name: Bjornstad syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by early onset of hearing loss and hair loss due to pili torti, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the BCS1L gene on chromosome 2q35.

name: Blau syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by familial granulomatous arthritis, uveitis and skin granulomas. It has_material_basis_in mutations in the NOD2/CARD15 genes.

name: blue cone monochromacy
descr: An achromatopsia that is characterized by severely impaired color discrimination, low visual acuity, nystagmus, photophobia due to the absence of functional long wavelength-sensitive and medium wavelength-sensitive cones in the retina and has_material_basis_in recessive X-linked inheritance.

name: Boomerang dysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by severe dwarfism, dislocated joints, club feet, distinctive facies and dysplastic tubular bones with boomerang-like bowing, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the FLNB gene on chromosome 3p14.

name: Borjeson-Forssman-Lehmann syndrome
descr: An X-linked disease that is characterized by intellectual disability, truncal obesity, seizures, hypogonadism, developmental delay, distinctive facial features, tapered fingers and short toes and has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive inheritance of mutations in the PHF6 gene.

name: Athabaskan brainstem dysgenesis syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by brainstem dysgenesis, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutations in the HOXA1 gene.

name: Bothnia retinal dystrophy
descr: A fundus dystrophy that is characterized by early onset of night blindness and decreased visual acuity that progresses to blindness in early adulthood, has_material_basis_in mutation in RLBP1 gene.

name: Bowen-Conradi syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by growth delays, failure to thrive and malformations of the head and face that results in infantile death, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the EMG1 gene on chromosome 12p13.

name: small cell carcinoma
descr: A carcinoma that is an undifferentiated neoplasm composed of primitive-appearing cells.

name: organ system cancer
descr: A cancer that is classified based on the organ it starts in.

name: cell type cancer
descr: A cancer that is classified by the type of cell from which it is derived.

name: anal canal cancer
descr: A large intestine cancer that is located_in the terminal part of the large intestine.

name: brachydactyly-syndactyly syndrome
descr: An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by brachydactyly and syndactyly, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the HOXD13 gene on chromosome 2q31.

name: brachyolmia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia characterized by generalized platyspondyly without significant long bone abnormalities and short stature.

name: branchiooculofacial syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by low birth weight and growth retardation, bilateral branchial clefts.

name: Brody myopathy
descr: A neuromuscular disease is characterized by difficulty relaxing muscles and muscle stiffness following exercise or other strenuous activity and is located in skeletal muscles.

name: Brooke-Spiegler syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by the development of several types of tumors from the skin, has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CYLD gene on chromosome 16q12.

name: Brown-Vialetto-Van Laere syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by progressive bulbar palsies with sensorineural deafness.

name: malignant pleural solitary fibrous tumor
descr: A pleural cancer that is located_in mesenchymal cells in the areolar tissue subjacent to the mesothelial-lined pleura.

name: fetal alcohol spectrum disorder
descr: A specific developmental disorder and physical disorder that is characterized by physical, behavioral and learning birth defects resulting from maternal ingestion of alcohol during pregnancy.

name: chorioamnionitis
descr: A placenta disease that is an inflammation of the fetal membranes (amnion and chorion) due to a bacterial infection.

name: funisitis
descr: A connective tissue disease that is an inflammation of the connective tissue of the umbilical cord.

name: Dent disease
descr: A renal tubular transport disease that is characterized by  tubular proteinuria, hypercalciuria, calcium nephrolithiasis, nephrocalcinosis and chronic kidney failure and has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive inheritance of mutations in the CLCN5 gene or OCRL1 gene.

name: cardiomyopathy
descr: A heart disease and a myopathy that is characterized by deterioration of the function of the heart muscle.

name: electroclinical syndrome
descr: An epilepsy syndrome that is a group of clinical entities showing a cluster of electro-clinical characteristics, classified according to age at onset, cognitive and developmental antecedents and consequences, motor and sensory examinations, EEG features, provoking or triggering factors, and patterns of seizure occurrence with respect to sleep.

name: neonatal period electroclinical syndrome
descr: An electroclinical syndrome with onset in the neonatal period less than 44 weeks of gestational age.

name: infancy electroclinical syndrome
descr: An electroclinical syndrome with onset in infancy occurring between birth and one year of age.

name: childhood electroclinical syndrome
descr: An electroclinical syndrome with onset in childhood between one and 12 years of age.

name: adolescence-adult electroclinical syndrome
descr: An electroclinical syndrome with onset in adolescence and adulthood.

name: variable age at onset electroclinical syndrome
early onset absence epilepsy
descr: A childhood electroclinical syndrome characterized by the occurrence of typical absence seizures starting between the age of four and ten years.

name: early infantile epileptic encephalopathy
descr: A neonatal period electroclinical syndrome that is characterized by tonic spasms and partial seizures.

name: 3-Methylcrotonyl-CoA carboxylase deficiency
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that is classified by inadequate levels of the enzyme 3-methylcrotonyl-CoA carboxylase that helps break down proteins containing the amino acid leucine. This disease has_symptom muscular hypotonia (weak muscle tone), has_symptom muscular atrophy, has_symptom feeding difficulties, has_symptom recurrent episodes of vomiting and diarrhea, and has_symptom lethargy.

name: aceruloplasminemia
descr: An iron metabolism disease that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the ceruloplasmin gene characterized by progressive neurodegeneration of the retina and basal ganglia and diabetes mellitus.

name: AGAT deficiency
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the GATM gene resulting in deficiency of arginine:glycine amidinotransferase which then limits creatine synthesis.

name: fatal infantile cardioencephalomyopathy due to cytochrome c oxidase deficiency
descr: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that has_material_basis_in a deficiency of cytochrome c oxidase.

name: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblC
descr: A methylmalonic acidemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency in synthesis of both AdoCbl and MeCbl (cblC) and is characterized by decreased levels of the coenzymes adenosylcobalamin (AdoCbl) and methylcobalamin (MeCbl), which results in decreased activity of the respective enzymes methylmalonyl-CoA mutase.

name: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblD
descr: A methylmalonic aciduria that is characterized by combined homocystinuria and methylmalonic aciduria and deficiency of MCM and MS activities.

name: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblF
descr: A methylmalonic acidemia that is characterized by the accumulation of cobalamin in lysosomes which is then unable to synthesize the cofactors adenosylcobalamin (AdoCbl) and methylcobalamin (MeCbl) and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the LMBRD1 gene on chromosome 6q13.

name: vitamin metabolic disorder
descr: An inherited metabolic disorder resulting from a deficiency in vitamin or vitamin cofactor transport or metabolism.

name: cerebral folate receptor alpha deficiency
descr: A vitamin metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in mutations in the folate receptor 1 (FOLR1) gene coding for folate receptor alpha (FRalpha), is located_in the brain and is characterized by progressive movement disturbance, psychomotor decline, and epilepsy.

name: ornithine translocase deficiency
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that has_material_basis in deficiency of ornithine translocase resulting in the accumulation of ammonia in the blood.

name: serine deficiency
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in defects in the biosynthesis of the amino acid L-serine.

name: PHGDH deficiency
descr: A serine deficiency that has_material_basis_in deficiency of phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase which results in a disruption of L-serine biosynthesis.

name: PSAT deficiency
descr: A serine deficiency that has_material_basis_in deficiency of phosphoserine aminotransferase and is characterized by low concentartions of serine and flycine in plasma and cerebrospinal fluid.

name: PSPH deficiency
descr: A serine deficiency that has_material_basis_in deficiency of phosphoserine phosphatase impeding the synthesis of L-serine.

name: tyrosinemia type II
descr: A tyrosinemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency of hepatic tyrosine aminotransferase located_in the liver and is characterized by keratitis, painful palmoplantar hyperkeratosis, mental retardation, and elevated serum tyrosine levels.

name: tyrosinemia type I
descr: A tyrosinemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency of the enzyme fumarylacetoacetate hydrolase resulting in an increase in fumarylacetoacetate which inhibits previous steps in tyrosine degradation leading to an accumulation of tyrosine in the body.

name: tyrosinemia type III
descr: A tyrosinemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency of 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate dioxygenase disrupting the break down of tyrosine.

name: glycogen metabolism disorder
descr: A carbohydrate metabolism disorder that is characterized by abnormal accumulation or depletion of liver glycogen.

name: neutral lipid storage disease
descr: A lipid storage disease that is characterized by accumulation of triglycerides in the cytoplasm of leukocytes, muscle, liver, fibroblasts, and other tissues.

name: coenzyme Q10 deficiency disease
descr: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by a deficiency of CoQ10 resulting from reduced biosynthesis.

name: vitamin B12 deficiency
descr: A vitamin metabolic disorder that results from low blood levels of vitamin B12.

name: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblE
descr: A methylmalonic acidemia that is characterized by megaloblastic anemia, lethargy, failure to thrive, developmental delay, intellectual deficit and seizures, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the MTRR on chromosome 5p15 that causes inborn error of vitamin B12 metabolism.

name: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblG
descr: A methylmalonic acidemia that is characterized by megaloblastic anemia, lethargy, failure to thrive, developmental delay, intellectual deficit and seizures, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the MTR gene on chromosome 1q43 that causes an inborn error of vitamin B12 metabolism.

name: congenital intrinsic factor deficiency
descr: A vitamin B12 deficiency that is characterized by megaloblastic anemia due to the absence of gastric intrinsic factor which results in abnormal vitamin B12 absorption.

name: X-linked monogenic disease
descr: A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in muations in genes on the X chromosome.

name: autosomal dominant disease
descr: An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by the presence of one disease-associated mutation of a gene which is sufficient to cause the disease.

name: autosomal recessive disease
descr: An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by the presence of two mutated copies of the gene, both of which must be present in order for the disease or trait to develop.

name: Y-linked monogenic disease
descr: A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in muations on the Y chromosome.

name: autosomal genetic disease
descr: A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in a mutation in a single gene on one of the non-sex chromosomes.

name: Qazi Markouizos syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by hypotonia, congenital fiber type disproportion and dysharmonic skeletal maturation.

name: alcohol dependence
descr: A substance dependence that is characterized by tolerance, withdrawal symptoms, increasing use, persistent desire to decrease consumption, time spent obtaining or recovering from alcohol caused by a physical and psychological dependence on alcohol.

name: nicotine dependence
descr: A substance dependence that is characterized by a physical dependence on nicotine.

name: mature T-cell and NK-cell lymphoma
descr: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma that has_material_basis_in mature T lymphocytes and natural killer cells.

name: anaplastic large cell lymphoma
descr: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma involving aberrant T-cells.

name: diffuse large B-cell lymphoma
descr: A B-cell lymphoma that is a cancer of B cells presenting as an aggressive tumour which can arise in virtually any part of the body.

name: mantle cell lymphoma
descr: A B-cell lymphocytic neoplasm due to CD5 positive antigen-naive pregerminal center B-cell within the mantle zone that surrounds normal germinal center follicles.

name: lymphoplasmacytic lymphoma
descr: A B-cell lymphocytic neoplasm characterized by an uncontrolled increase of B-cells.

name: marginal zone B-cell lymphoma
descr: A B-cell lymphoma that is characterized by initial formation in the marginal zones of lymph tissue.

name: peripheral T-cell lymphoma
descr: A mature T-cell and NK-cell lymphoma includes a group of T-cell lymphomas that develop away from the thymus.

name: splenic marginal zone lymphoma
descr: A marginal zone B-cell lymphocyte located_in the spleen comprised of B-cells in place of white pulp.

name: T-cell large granular lymphocyte leukemia
descr: A chronic lymphocytic leukemia that exhibits an unexplained, chronic (> 6 months) elevation in large granular lymphocytes (LGLs) in the peripheral blood.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 8
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the VAPB gene on chromosome 20.

name: cerebellar ataxia
descr: A hereditary ataxia that is characterized by ataxia originating in the cerebellum.

name: ataxia with oculomotor apraxia type 1
descr: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive cerebellar ataxia including oculomotor apraxia, severe neuropathy and hypoalbuminemia, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the APTX gene.

name: ataxia with oculomotor apraxia type 2
descr: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by the onset of ataxia between age three and thirty including axonal sensorimotor neuropathy, oculomotor apraxia, cerebellar atrophy and elevated alpha-fetoprotein, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the SETX gene on chromosome 9q34.

name: deafness-dystonia-optic neuronopathy syndrome
descr: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by hearing loss that begins early in life, problems with movement, impaired vision, and behavior problems, and has_material_basis_in mutations in the TIMM8A gene resulting in abnormal protein transport within the mitochondria.

name: metabolic acidosis
descr: An acquired metabolic disease that characterized by excessive production of acid.

name: myotonic dystrophy type 2
descr: A myotonic disease that is characterized by myotonia and progressive, proximal muscle wasting and weakness affecting the skeletal and smooth muscles of the neck, shoulders, elbows and hips and has_material_basis_in the autosomal dominant inheritance of the CNBP (ZNF9) gene containing an expansion of a CCTG repeat in intron one.

name: X-linked myopathy with excessive autophagy
descr: A myopathy that is characterized by childhood onset of progressive muscle weakness and atrophy primarily affecting the proximal muscles in males between 5 and 10 years old, has_material_basis_in mutation in the VMA21 gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: adenylosuccinase lyase deficiency
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that is characterized by microcephaly, aggressive behavior, cerebellar hypoplasia and seizures, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the ADSL gene resulting in adenylosuccinate lyase deficiency.

name: ARC syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by congenital joint contractures, renal tubular dysfunction, cholestasis, severe failure to thrive, ichthyosis and a defect in platelet alpha-granule biogenesis and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS33B gene or homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VIPAR gene on chromosome 14q24.3.

name: Armfield syndrome
descr: A syndromic X-linked intellectual disability characterized by intellectual disability, short stature, seizures, and small hands and feet  and in some cases cleft palate or cataracts/glaucoma that has_material_basis_in variation in the chromosomal region Xq28.

name: neuroacanthocytosis
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by acanthocytosis, chorea, progressive cognitive impairment, muscle weakness and seizures, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS13A gene, which encodes chorein, on chromosome 9q21.

name: choreaacanthocytosis
descr: A neuroacanthocytosis characterized by progressive neurodegeneration and red cell acanthocytosis, with onset in the third to fifth decade of life and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS13A gene, which encodes chorein, on chromosome 9q21.

name: midface dysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by hypertelorism, a wide nose, vertical midline cleft and encephalocele.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency, nuclear type 1
descr: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATPAF2 gene on chromosome 17p11.

name: N syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by intellectual disability, deafness, ocular abnormalities, T-cell leukemia, cryptorchidism, hypospadias and spasticity.

name: polycystic liver disease
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by the presence of multiple cysts located_in the liver.

name: pheochromocytoma
descr: An endocrine organ benign neoplasm that arises within the adrenal medulla, releasing epinephrines and norepinephrines hormones that cause either episodic or persistent high blood pressure.

name: spastic ataxia 1
descr: A spastic ataxia characterized by early-onset cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, pyramidal syndrome and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of heterozygous mutation in the VAMP1 gene on chromosome 12p13.

name: paraganglioma
descr: A pheochromocytoma that arises in extraadrenal sympathetic ganglia.

name: rapadilino syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by radial ray defect, patellae hypoplasia, cleft palate, diarrhea, dislocated joints, limb malformations, long nose and normal intelligence, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DNA helicase gene RECQL4 on chromosome 8q24.

name: schneckenbecken dysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by hypoplastic iliac bones, hypoplastic vertebral bodies, short ribs and broad long bones, prenatally lethal, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the SLC35D1 gene on chromosome 1p31.

name: non-syndromic X-linked intellectual disability
descr: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by a X-linked inheritance pattern.

name: Joubert syndrome
descr: A ciliopathy that is characterized by congenital malformation of the brainstem and agenesis or hypoplasia of the cerebellar vermis leading to an abnormal respiratory pattern, nystagmus, hypotonia, ataxia, and delay in achieving motor milestones.

name: Meckel syndrome
descr: A ciliopathy that is characterized by renal cystic dysplasia, occipital encephalocele, polydactyly (post axial), hepatic developmental defects, and pulmonary hypoplasia.

name: hydrolethalus syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by mulitple fetal developmental defects including polydactyly and central nervous system malformations that results from a single amino acid mutation of D211G of the HYLS1 gene which plays a central role in cilia formation.

name: Opitz-GBBB syndrome
descr: A monogenic disease that is characterized by hypertelorism, hypospadias, and additional midline defects resulting from mutations to the MID1 gene in the X-linked form or from a deletion on chromosome 22q11.2 in the autosomal dominant form.

name: Ogden syndrome
descr: An X-linked disease characterized by postnatal growth failure, severely delayed psychomotor development, variable dysmorphic features, and hypotonia and has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive or X-linked dominant mutation in the NAA10 gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: Zollinger-Ellison syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is haracterized by the development of a one or more tumors (gastrinoma) in the pancreas, duodenum, or both that secrete excessive levels of gastrin, a hormone that stimulates production of acid by the stomach.

name: secondary progressive multiple sclerosis
descr: A multiple sclerosis that is characterised by a worsening of disability, rather than by relapses followed by recovery, which progressively worsens until a steady progression of disability replaces the cycles of attacks.

name: primary progressive multiple sclerosis
descr: A multiple sclerosis that is characterized by steady worsening of neurologic functioning, without any distinct relapses or periods of remission. The rate of progression may vary over time, with occasional plateaus or temporary improvements, but the progression is continuous.

name: progressive relapsing multiple sclerosis
descr: A multiple sclerosis that is characterized by steadily worsening symptoms and attacks during periods of remission with disease progression from the onset.

name: iridogoniodysgenesis syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by the iris stroma being hypoplastic resulting from abnormalities in the differentiation of the anterior segment structures and increased values of intraocular pressure and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutations in the PITX2 gene.

name: juvenile polyposis syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by predisposition to hamartomatous benign polyps in the gastrointestinal tract, specifically in the stomach, small intestine, colon, and rectum.

name: proximal symphalangism
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by ankylosis of the proximal interphalangeal joints, carpal and tarsal bone fusion, and conductive deafness.

name: tarsal-carpal coalition syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by fusion of the carpals, tarsals, and phalanges, short first metacarpals causing brachydactyly; and humeroradial fusion.

name: fibular hypoplasia and complex brachydactyly
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterised by severe reduction or absence of the fibula and complex brachydactyly.

name: persistent Mullerian duct syndrome
descr: A pseudohermaphroditism that is characterized by the persistence of Mullerian duct derivatives (i.e. uterus, cervix, fallopian tubes and upper two thirds of vagina) in a phenotypically and karyotypically male.

name: multiple cutaneous and mucosal venous malformations
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by multiple bluish cutaneous or mucosal venous lesions.

name: short QT syndrome
descr: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by heart arrhythmia defined as a short QT interval on an EKG (less than 300 ms) that does not significantly change with heart rate, tall and peaked T waves, and a structurally normal heart.

name: multiple synostoses syndrome
descr: A dysostosis that is characterized by premature joint ankylosis and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inhertitance.

name: cone dystrophy
descr: A retinal disease that is characterized by the loss of cone cells, the photoreceptors responsible for both central and color vision.

name: achalasia microcephaly syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by microcephaly, intellectual deficit and early onset symptoms of achalasia (abnormal enlargement of the esophagus, impaired peristalsis, cardiospasm, recurrent vomiting and respiratory infections).

name: peroxisomal acyl-CoA oxidase deficiency
descr: A peroxisomal disease that is characterized by hypotonia and seizures in the neonatal period and neurological regression in early infancy.

name: cerebral creatine deficiency syndrome
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that is characterized by mental retardation, severe speech delay, behavioral abnormalities and seizures, has_material_basis_in mutation in the creatine transporter gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: guanidinoacetate methyltransferase deficiency
descr: A cerebral creatine deficiency syndrome that is characterized by severe intellectual disability, seizures, speech problems and involuntary movements, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the GAMT gene on chromosome 19p13.

name: creatine transporter deficiency
descr: A cerebral creatine deficiency syndrome that is characterized by mental retardation, severe speech delay, behavioral abnormalities and seizures, has_material_basis_in mutation in the SLC6A8 gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: androgenic alopecia
descr: An alopecia that is characterized by M-shaped hair line recession and thinning of hair at the crown of the head in males.

name: Ehlers-Danlos syndrome progeroid type
descr: An Ehlers-Danlos syndrome that is characterized by aged appearance, developmental delay, short stature, craniofacial disproportion, generalized osteopenia, defective wound healing, hypermobile joints, hypotonic muscles, and loose but elastic skin and has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the B3GALT6 gene.

name: glioblastoma classical subtype
descr: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by abnormally high levels of epidermal growth factor receptor and the absence of p53 mutations.

name: glioblastoma proneural subtype
descr: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by IDH1 and p53 mutations and Platelet Derived Growth Factor A amplification.

name: glioblastoma mesenchymal subtype
descr: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by the most frequent number of mutation of the Neurofibromin 1 gene.

name: glioblastoma neural subtype
descr: A glioblastoma multiforme that is characterized by the expression of several gene types that are also typical of the brain's normal, noncancerous nerve cells, or neurons.

name: Kahrizi syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by mental retardation, cataracts, coloboma, kyphosis, and coarse facial features and has_material_basis_in mutation in the SRD5A3 gene.

name: mucopolysaccharidosis IX
descr: A mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency in hyaluronidase.

name: biotin deficiency
descr: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by thinning of the hair (often with loss of hair color), and red scaly rash around the eyes, nose, and mouth.

name: congenital adrenal hyperplasia
descr: A steroid inherited metabolic disorder that is characterized by adrenal insufficiency and variable degrees of hyper or hypo androgeny manifestations resulting from steroidogenic enzyme deficiency.

name: spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia, Pakistani type
descr: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that is characterized by short stature, short and bowed lower limbs, mild brachydactyly, kyphoscoliosis, abnormal gait, enlarged knee joints, precocious osteoarthropathy, and normal intelligence.

name: spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia with congenital joint dislocations
descr: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that is characterized by short stature of prenatal onset, joint dislocations (knees, hips, radial heads), club feet, and limitation of range of motion that can involve all large joints.

name: temtamy preaxial brachydactyly syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by brachydactyly, hyperphalangism of digits, facial dysmorphism, dental anomalies, sensorineural hearing loss, delayed motor and mental development, and growth retardation and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CHSY1 gene.

name: eye adnexa disease
descr: An eye and adnexa disease that is located_in the adnexa of the eye.

name: urofacial syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by inverted facial expressions in association with a severe and early-onset form of dysfunctional urinary voiding.

name: Stargardt disease
descr: An age related macular degeneration that is characterized by progressive vision loss usually to the point of legal blindness.

name: transcobalamin II deficiency
descr: A vitamin B12 deficiency that is characterized by a lack of vitamin B12 intestinal absorption resulting from a deficiency in the B12 transport protein TCII.

name: Matthew-Wood syndrome
descr: An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by microphthalmia or anophthalmia, pulmonary agenesis, and diaphragmatic defect.

name: atrioventricular block
descr: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by the impairment of the conduction between the atria and ventricles of the heart.

name: first-degree atrioventricular block
descr: An atrioventricular block that is characterized by prolonged PR interval on electrocardiogram caused by delayed conduction from atria to ventricles through the atrioventricular node.

name: second-degree atrioventricular block
descr: An atrioventricular block that is characterized by progressive prolongation of the PR interval on consecutive beats followed by a blocked P wave on electrocardiogram or intermittently non-conducted P waves not preceded by PR changes on electrocardiogram caused by a conduction block between the atria and the ventricles through the atrioventricular node.

name: third-degree atrioventricular block
descr: An atrioventricular block that is characterized by bradycardia, hypotension, hemodynamic instability and complete dissociation between P waves and QRS complexes on electrocardiogram caused when conduction fails to propagate from atria to ventricles.

name: sinoatrial node disease
descr: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by dysfunction of the impulse-generating (pacemaker) tissue located in the right atrium of the heart which generates normal sinus rhythm.

name: endocardium disease
descr: A heart disease that is located_in the innermost layer of tissue that lines the chambers of the heart.

name: tricuspid valve disease
descr: A heart valve disease that is characterized by valvular insufficiency or valvular stenosis, located_in tricuspid valve between the right atrium and right ventricle.

name: rheumatic heart disease
descr: A heart valve disease that is characterized by repeated inflammation with fibrinous repair caused by an autoimmune reaction to Group A beta-hemolytic streptococci (GAS) that results in valvular damage. The cardinal anatomic changes of the valve include leaflet thickening, commissural fusion, and shortening and thickening of the tendinous cords.

name: artery disease
descr: A vascular disease that is located_in an artery.

name: pericardium disease
descr: A cardiovascular system disease that is located_in the  fibrous sac surrounding the heart.

name: peripheral artery disease
descr: An artery disease that is characterized by build up of plaque in the arteries that carry blood to your head, organs, and limbs.

name: familial encephalopathy with neuroserpin inclusion bodies
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by intraneuronal inclusions of mutant neuroserpin resulting in progressive encephalopathy, dementia and seizures and has_material_basis_in a mutation in the SERPINI1 gene inherited in an in autosomal dominant pattern.

name: pyrimidine metabolic disorder
descr: An inherited metabolic disorder involving dysfunction of pyrimidine metabolism.

name: orotic aciduria
descr: A pyrimidine metabolic disorder that is characterized by an excessive secretion of orotic acid in urine.

name: CHARGE syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is acterized by a pattern of congenital anomalies including choanal atresia and malformations of the heart, inner ear, and retina.

name: generalized dystonia
descr: A dystonia that affects most or all of the body.

name: focal dystonia
descr: A dystonia that is localized to a specific part of the body.

name: multifocal dystonia
descr: A dystonia that involves two or more unrelated body parts.

name: segmental dystonia
descr: A dystonia that affects two or more adjacent parts of the body.

name: anismus
descr: A focal dystonia that is characterized by the failure of the pelvic floor muscles to relax during defecation.

name: cervical dystonia
descr: A focal dystonia that is characterized by simultaneous contraction of the agonist and antagonist muscles that control the position of the head contracting during dystonic movement which causes the neck to involuntarily turn to the left, right, upwards, and/or downwards.

name: focal hand dystonia
descr: A focal dystonia that affects a single muscle or small group of muscles in the hand resulting from involuntary muscular contractions.

name: oculogyric crisis
descr: A focal dystonia that is characterized by a prolonged involuntary upward deviation of the eyes.

name: oromandibular dystonia
descr: A focal dystonia that is characterized by distortions of the mouth and tongue.

name: spasmodic dystonia
descr: A focal dystonia that involves the muscles that control the vocal cords, resulting in strained or breathy speech.

name: cranio-facial dystonia
descr: A focal dystonia that is characterized as dystonia that affects the muscles of the head, face, and neck.

name: hemidystonia
descr: A multifocal dystonia that involves the arm and leg on the same side of the body.

name: sleep apnea
descr: A sleep disorder characterized by repeated cessation and commencing of breathing that repeatedly disrupts sleep.

name: obstructive sleep apnea
descr: A sleep apnea that is characterized by repeated collapse and obstruction of the upper airway during sleep, which results in reduced airflow (hypopnea) or complete airflow cessation (apnea), oxygen desaturation, and arousals from sleep.

name: periampullary adenoma
descr: An ampulla of Vater neoplasm that is characterized by glandular dysplastic lesion having pre-malignant potential.

name: diabetic encephalopathy
descr: A brain disease that is characterized by functional impairment of cognition, cerebral signal conduction, neurotransmission and synaptic plasticity, and underlying structural pathology associated with diabetes.

name: glomerulosclerosis
descr: A glomerulonephritis that is characterized by hardening of the glomerulus in the kidney.

name: limb ischemia
descr: An ischemia that is characterized by low blood supply to tissues in the limb due to interruption in the arterial blood supply.

name: chronic venous insufficiency
descr: A venous insufficiency that is characterized by lower extremity swelling, hyperpigmentation, pruritus and venous ulceration caused by blood pooling in the veins.

name: renal fibrosis
descr: A kidney disease that is characterized by progressive detrimental connective tissue deposition of the kidney parenchyma leading to deterioration of renal function.

name: oppositional defiant disorder
descr: A specific developmental disorder that is characterized by a pattern of angry mood, defiant behavior and vindictiveness in children and adolescents.

name: Perrault syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disesase that is characterized by sensorineural hearing loss and ovarian failure.

name: Marshall-Smith syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by advanced bone age, failure to thrive, respiratory problems, dysmorphic facial features, and variable mental retardation.

name: hemorrhagic cystitis
descr: A cystitis that is characterized by dysuria, hematuria and hemorrhage located_in the lower urinary tract.

name: colorectal adenoma
descr: An intestinal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin and is located_in colon and located_in rectum.

name: colorectal adenocarcinoma
descr: A colorectal carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: pyometritis
descr: A uterine disease that is characterized by inflammation of the uterus and is associated with pus in the uterine cavity.

name: arteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
descr: An anterior ischemic optic neuropathy that is characterized by near-complete vision loss caused by damage to the medium-sized blood vessels supplying the optic nerves following temporal arteritis.

name: non-arteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
descr: An anterior ischemic optic neuropathy that is characterized by near-complete vision loss caused by acute ischemic damage to the optic nerve due to non-inflammatory small vessel disease.

name: tongue squamous cell carcinoma
descr: A head and neck squamous cell carcinoma that is located_in the tongue.

name: oral squamous cell carcinoma
descr: An oral cavity cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: hepatocellular adenoma
descr: A liver benign neoplasm that is located_in liver cells and that is composed_of epithelial tissue in which tumor cells form glands or glandlike structures.

name: villous adenoma
descr: An adenoma that is located_in the colon and other places in the gastrointestinal tract and sometimes in other parts of the body.

name: in situ pulmonary adenocarcinoma
descr: A lung cancer that derives_from the distal bronchioles or alveoli that initially exhibit a specific non-invasive growth pattern.

name: fibroma
descr: A connective tissue benign neoplasm composed of fibrous or connective tissues that derives_from mesenchymal tissue.

name: large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma
descr: A lung large cell carcinoma that derives_from neuroendocrine cells.

name: follicular lymphoma
descr: A B-cell lymphoma that is characterized as an indolent non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and has_material_basis_in follicle center B-cells (centrocytes and centroblasts).

name: Caroli disease
descr: A bile duct disease that is characterized by abnormal dilatation of the intrahepatic bile ducts.

name: pancreatic agenesis
descr: A pancreas disease that is characterized by the failure of the pancreas to develop prior to birth.

name: fragile X-associated tremor/ataxia syndrome
descr: A X-linked hereditary ataxia that is characterized by adult-onset progressive intention tremor and gait ataxia, has_material_basis_in expanded trinucleotide repeat of the FMR1 gene that results_in a toxic gain of function of FMR1 RNA.

name: Koolen de Vries syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by developmental delay, intellectual disability, muscle weakness (hypotonia), epilepsy, distinctive facial features and congenital malformations of the heart, urogenital tract and the central nervous system, and has_material_basis_in either a chromosome 17 (17q21.31) microdeletion or a mutation in the KANSL1-gene.

name: inclusion body myopathy with Paget disease of bone and frontotemporal dementia
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by progressive proximal muscle weakness, steolytic bone lesions consistent with Paget disease, and frontotemporal dementia and has_material_basis_in mutation in the valosin containing protein.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 5
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by the early-onset of cerebellar signs and eye movement abnormalities with a very slow disease progression, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the SPTBN2 gene.

name: infantile cerebellar-retinal degeneration
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by onset between ages 2 and 6 months of truncal hypotonia, athetosis, seizures, and ophthalmologic abnormalities, particularly optic atrophy and retinal degeneration.

name: triosephosphate isomerase deficiency
descr: A glucose metabolism disorder that is characterized by chronic haemolytic anaemia, cardiomyopathy, susceptibility to infections and severe neurological dysfunction, and has_material_basis_in the triosephosphate isomerase enzyme (TPI1) gene inherited as an autosomal recessive trait.

name: IMAGe syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by intrauterine growth restriction, metaphyseal dysplasia, adrenal hypoplasia congenita, genital abnormalities and has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CDKN1C gene.

name: Troyer syndrome
descr: A hereditary spastic paraplegia that is characterized by spasticity of the leg muscles, progressive muscle weakness, paraplegia, muscle wasting in the hands and feet (distal amyotrophy), small stature, developmental delay, learning disorders, speech difficulties (dysarthria), and mood swings, and has_material_basis_in a mutation of the SPG20 gene.

name: Townes-Brocks syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by imperforate anus, dysplastic ears often associated with sensorineural and/or conductive hearing impairment, and thumb malformations.

name: syndromic intellectual disability
descr: An intellectual disability that is characterized by the presence of associated medical and behavioral sign and symptoms.

name: non-syndromic intellectual disability
descr: An intellectual disability that is characterized by the absence of associated medical and behavioral signs and symptoms.

name: synucleinopathy
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by the abnormal accumulation of aggregates of alpha-synuclein protein in neurons, nerve fibres or glial cells.

name: adrenal cortical adenoma
descr: An adrenal adenoma that is a benign tumor of the adrenal cortex.

name: adrenal gland pheochromocytoma
descr: A malignant pheochromocytoma that is characterized by overproduction of adrenaline.

name: gallbladder adenoma
descr: A biliary tract benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin located_in the gallbladder.

name: ameloblastoma
descr: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in odontogenic epithelium.

name: bone ameloblastoma
descr: A bone benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in odontogenic epithelium and is located_in bone.

name: bone squamous cell carcinoma
descr: A bone carcinoma that derives_from squamous epithelial cells.

name: bone chondrosarcoma
descr: A chondrosarcoma that is located_in bone.

name: phalanx chondroma
descr: A bone benign neoplasm that is located_in the phalanx that has_material_basis_in cartilaginous cells.

name: brain stem medulloblastoma
descr: A brain stem cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

name: sacrum chordoma
descr: A spinal chordoma that is located_in the sacrum.

name: corpus callosum oligodendroglioma
descr: A brain oligodendroglioma located_in the corpus callosum.

name: medulloblastoma
descr: An infratentorial cancer that is located_in the lower part of the brain and is a type of primitive neuroectodermal tumor.

name: parietal lobe ependymoma
descr: A parietal lobe neoplasm that has_material_basis_in cells lining the ventricles of the brain.

name: salivary gland carcinoma
descr: A salivary gland cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: inflammatory myofibroblastic tumor
descr: A mesenchymal cell neoplasm that has_material_basis_in myofibroblastic cells admixed with inflammatory cells.

name: conjunctival nevus
descr: A sensory organ benign neoplasm that is located in the eye conjunctiva.

name: mixed extragonadal germ cell cancer
descr: A mixed germ cell cancer that is located_in areas of the body other than the ovary or testicle.

name: myelodysplastic syndrome
descr: A bone marrow cancer that is characterized by under production of white blood cells, red blood cells and platelets.

name: MALT lymphoma
descr: A marginal zone B-cell lymphoma that has_material_basis_in mucosal tissue involved in antibody production.

name: cecum adenoma
descr: A cecal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: appendix carcinoid tumor
descr: An appendix cancer that has_material_basis_in neurodendocrine cells.

name: colon adenoma
descr: A colonic benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: large intestine adenocarcinoma
descr: A large intestine cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: large intestine adenoma
descr: An intestinal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin and is located_in the large intestine.

name: rectum adenoma
descr: An rectal neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: bronchus mucoepidermoid carcinoma
descr: A bronchus cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells, mucus-secreting cells, and intermediate cells.

name: lung combined type small cell adenocarcinoma
descr: A lung combined type small cell carcinoma that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin.

name: vaginal carcinoma
descr: A vaginal cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: trachea mucoepidermoid carcinoma
descr: A trachea carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of squamous cells, mucus-secreting cells, and intermediate cells.

name: tonsil squamous cell carcinoma
descr: A tonsil cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: pharynx squamous cell carcinoma
descr: A pharynx cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: gastrointestinal carcinoma
descr: A gastrointestinal system cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: spindle epithelial tumor with thymus-like differentiation tumor
descr: A thyroid gland carcinoma that has_material_basis_in compact bundles of long spindle epithelial cells that merge with tubulopapillary structures and/or mucinous glands.

name: striated muscle rhabdoid tumor
descr: A muscle cancer that is located_in striated muscle and has_material_basis_in rhabdoid cells which are large cells with eccentrically located nuclei and abundant, eosinophilic cytoplasm.

name: small intestine carcinoid neuroendocrine tumor
descr: A small intestine cancer that has_material_basis_in cells of the neuroendocrine system.

name: jejunal adenocarcinoma
descr: A jejunal cancer that is located_in the jejunum and has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue that has glandular origin.

name: duodenum adenoma
descr: A duodenal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: ovarian melanoma
descr: An ovarian cancer that has_material_basis_in melanoctyes.

name: mucosal melanoma
descr: A melanoma that has_material_basis_in melanocytes located_in mucosal membranes lining the respiratory, gastrointestinal and urogenital tract.

name: sublingual gland adenoid cystic carcinoma
descr: A sublingual gland cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures within the affected organ.

name: parotid gland adenoid cystic carcinoma
descr: A parotid gland cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures within the affected organ.

name: lung mucoepidermoid carcinoma
descr: A lung carcinoma that has_material_basis in a combination of squamous cells, mucus secreting cells and intermediate cells.

name: ovarian serous carcinoma
descr: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in the lining of the ovary and produces a serum-like fluid.

name: ovarian clear cell carcinoma
descr: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in cells with clear cytoplasm and glycogen secreting hob nail cells.

name: cervical neuroblastoma
descr: An extracranial neuroblastoma that has_material_basis_in immature nerve cells.

name: extra-adrenal pheochromocytoma
descr: A malignant pheochromocytoma that originate in the ganglia of the sympathetic nervous system and are named based upon the primary anatomical site of origin.

name: retroperitoneal neuroblastoma
descr: A retroperitoneal cancer that has_material_basis_in immature nerve cells.

name: breast lobular carcinoma
descr: A breast carcinoma that derives_from breast lobules (milk glands).

name: uterine corpus endometrial carcinoma
descr: A uterine corpus cancer that is derives_from the inner lining of the uterus.

name: endocervical adenocarcinoma
descr: An endocervical carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: spastic ataxia 2
descr: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia, spasticity and peripheral neuropathy in the first two decades of life, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KIF1C gene on chromosome 17p13.

name: spastic ataxia 3
descr: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, hyperreflexia, urinary urgency and dysarthria, has_material_basis_in  homozygous or compound heterozygous complex genomic rearrangements involving the MARS2 gene on chromosome 2q33.

name: spastic ataxia 4
descr: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, dysarthria and optic atrophy, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the MTPAP gene on chromosome 10p11.

name: spastic ataxia 5
descr: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by early onset of cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, oculomotor apraxia, dystonia and myoclonic epilepsy, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the AFG3L2 gene on chromosome 18p11.

name: spastic ataxia 7
descr: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by poor visual acuity, cerebellar ataxia, dysarthria and pyramidal signs.

name: Charlevoix-Saguenay spastic ataxia
descr: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by early onset of cerebellar ataxia, pyramidal tract signs and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the gene encoding the sacsin protein on chromosome 13q12.

name: hereditary hypophosphatemic rickets with hypercalciuria
descr: A rickets that has_material_basis_in increased serum 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D levels and increased intestinal calcium absorption and is characterized by the presence of hypophosphatemia secondary to renal phosphate wasting, radiographic and/or histologic evidence of rickets, limb deformities, muscle weakness, and bone pain.

name: autosomal dominant hypophosphatemic rickets
descr: A rickets characterized by low levels of serum phosphate and elevated levels of ALP and phosphaturia and that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: autosomal recessive hypophosphatemic rickets
descr: A rickets that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance mutation in the DMP1 gene and is characterized by hypophosphatemia, rickets and/or osteomalacia and slow growth.

name: autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia
descr: A hereditary ataxia that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: hereditary ataxia
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by slowly progressive incoordination of gait and often associated with poor coordination of hands, speech, and eye movements.

name: spastic ataxia
descr: A hereditary ataxia that is characterized by early onset of cerebellar ataxia, pyramidal tract signs and peripheral neuropathy.

name: X-linked hereditary ataxia
descr: A hereditary ataxia that is characterized by X-linked inheritance.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 1
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, dysarthria, dysphagia, dystonia and peripheral neuropathy that begins in early adulthood, has_material_basis_in the expanded (CAG)n trinucleotide repeat of ataxin-1 gene on chromosome 6p22.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 2
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, bulbar palsy, peripheral neuropathy chorea and muscle atrophy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 6
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progresive ataxia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the CACNA1A gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 4
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progresive ataxia, dysarthria and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the SCA4 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 7
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, progressive vision loss, and failure to thrive, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN7 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 8
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive dysarthria, bradykinesia, nystagmus and loss of coordination, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN80S gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 10
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by gait ataxia, upper-limb ataxia, dysarthria and dysphagia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN10 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 11
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, nystagmus, pyramidal abonormalities and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the TTBK2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 12
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by minor ataxia and intention tremor, has_material_basis_in CAG expansion of the PPP2R2B gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 13
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by developmental delay, ataxia, myoclinic jerks, dysarthria, dysphagia and seizure, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the KCNC3 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 14
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, dysarthria and dysphagia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the PRKCG gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 15
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, nystagmus, dysarthria and dysphagia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ITPR1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 17
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by chorea, dementia, dystonia, spasiticity and seizure, has_material_basis_in CAG repeat expansion in the TBP gene.

name: autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia, deafness and narcolepsy
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, sensorineal deafness, narcolepsy with cataplexy, and dementia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the DNMT1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 18
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia and sensory neuropathy, has_material_basis_in mutation on chromosome 7q22-q23.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 19/22
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by mild cerebellar ataxia, cognitive impairment, myoclonus and tremor.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 20
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar dysarthria.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 21
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive cerebellar ataxia, cognitive impairment, tremor, bradykinesia and rigidity.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 23
descr: An autosomal dominnant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia, dysarthria, slow saccades and hyperreflexia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the PDYN gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 25
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia and sensory neuropathy, has_material_basis_in repeat CAG expansion on chromosome 2p15-p21.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 26
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia and oculomotor abnormalities, has_material_basis_in mutation in the EEF2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 27
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia, early-onset tremor and dyskinesia, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the FGF14 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 28
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, dysarthria, hyperreflexia, ophthalmoparesis, nystagmus and ptosis, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the AFG3L2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 29
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, intellectual disability, dysarthria and ophthalmoplegia, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the ITPR1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 30
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive gait abnormalities and dysarthria, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ODZ3 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 31
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by late-onset ataxia, dysarthria and horizontal nystagmus, has_material_basis_in repeat expansion mutation in the BEAN1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 34
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by papulosquamous, ichthyosiform plaques at birth and progressive ataxia, dysarthria, nystagmus and hyporeflexia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ELOVL4 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 35
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by a slowly progressive ataxia, tremor, dysarthria and hyperreflexia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the TGM6 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 36
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, dysarthria, hyperreflexia, sensiorineural hearing loss and muscle atrophy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the NOP56 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 37
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia and dysarthria, presenting in mid-adulthood, and has_material_basis_in mutation to the DAB1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 38
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia and nystagmus, presenting in mid-adulthood, and has_material_basis_in mutation to the ELOVL5 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 40
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive gait abnormalutes, dysarthria, tremor and hyporeflexia, has_material_basis_in muation in the CCDC88C gene.

name: hypomyelinating leukoencephalopathy
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by nystagmus, spasticity, and a distinct pattern of MRI abnormalities.

name: GRID2-related spinocerebellar ataxia
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by cognitive delay, abnormal eye movements, and hearing loss.

name: episodic ataxia type 1
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by periodic ataxia and frequent myokymic discharges, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the potassium channel gene KCNA1.

name: episodic ataxia type 2
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by periodic ataxia and nystagmus, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the calcium channel gene CACNA1A.

name: episodic ataxia type 3
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by periodic ataxia, myokymia, vertigo and tinnitus, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: episodic ataxia type 4
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by vertigo and diplopia.

name: episodic ataxia type 5
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by dysarthria and vertigo, develops in early childhood, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the CACNB4 gene.

name: episodic ataxia type 6
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by nystagmus and dysarthria, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the SLC1A3 gene.

name: episodic ataxia type 7
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by episodes of weakness and dysarthria, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: episodic ataxia type 8
descr: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by weakness, dysarthria and myokymia, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the UBR4 gene.

name: cerebellar ataxia, mental retardation and dysequlibrium syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by congenital onset of nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia, disturbed equilibrium, and mental retardation, associated with cerebellar hypoplasia.

name: nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia with mental retardation
descr: A cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by early onset of nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia, developmental delay, intellectual impairment and cerebellar atrophy, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the CAMTA1 gene.

name: autosomal recessive spinocerebellar ataxia 10
descr: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, dysarthria, nystagmus and marked cerebellar atrophy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ANO10 gene.

name: infective endocarditis
descr: An endocarditis that is characterized by inflammation of the endocardium caused by infectious agents.

name: withdrawal disorder
descr: A substance-related disorder that occurs upon the abrupt discontinuation/separation or a decrease in dosage of the intake of medications, recreational drugs, and alcohol.

name: C1 inhibitor deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is a functional deficiency in the complement component C1 inhibitor leading to hereditary angioedema (HAE) involving swelling due to leakage of fluid from blood vessels into connective tissue.

name: autoimmune disease of central nervous system
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease located_in the central nervous system.

name: autoimmune disease of endocrine system
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system resulting in production of antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the endocrine system.

name: CD3zeta deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that affects the development and function of T cells.

name: janus kinase-3 deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by severe cell-mediated and antibody-mediated immunodeficiency with recurrent bacterial, viral, and fungal infections, develops_from janus kinase-3 deficiency, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the JAK3 gene of chromosome 19p13.11, responsible for normal differentiation and maturation of B and T immune cells.

name: MHC class I deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial, viral, and fungal infections, especially of the lung, and sterile necrotizing granulomas of the skin, develops_from deficiency or decreased surface expression of MHC Class I, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation affecting MHC Class I production or expression and frequently involves TAP1 and TAP2 subunits, and is typically asymptomatic in infancy.

name: Omenn syndrome
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis in the RAG1 and RAG2 genes on chromosome 11p and the Artemis gene on chromosome 10p. It is characterized by erythroderma, desquamation, alopecia, chronic diarrhea, failure to thrive, lymphadenopathy, and hepatosplenomegaly.

name: recombinase activating gene 1 deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on Chromosome 6 RAG1 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the T- and B-lymphocyte receptor genes.

name: recombinase activating gene 2 deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on Chromosome 6 RAG2 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the T- and B-lymphocyte receptor genes.

name: X-linked severe combined immunodeficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is a X-linked SCID that has_material_basis_in mutations in genes encoding common gamma chain proteins shared by the interleukin (IL-2,4,7,9,16 and21) receptors resulting in a non-functional gamma chain, defective interleukin signalling, minimal or ascent T- and NK cells and non-functional B-cells.

name: CD45 deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive disease with T and B lymphocyte dysfunction, due to a large deletion at one allelle and a point mutation at the other. The point mutation resulted in the alteration of intervening sequence 13 donor splice site. The population of T lymphocytes is diminished and unresponsive to mitogen stimulation. The level of B lymphocyte numbers, serum immunoglobulin decreased with age.

name: interleukin-7 receptor alpha deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that results from defective IL7R expression causes T-B+NK+ SCID. Loss of IL-7R function leads to the loss of an antiapoptotic signal, resulting in a loss of T-cell selection in thymus.

name: CD3delta deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by the absence of T cells but normal numbers of B cells. CD3D is essential for T cell development.

name: CD3epsilon deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive mutations in the gene coding for T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3epsilon chain precursors. Patients with CD3epsilon deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the T-cell receptor CD3-complex.

name: CD3gamma deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive mutations in the gene coding for T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3gamma chain precursors.  Patients with CD3gamma deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the T-cell receptor CD3-complex. Affected patients have decreased T-cell numbers and function; B cells are variably affected.

name: coronin-1A deficiency
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an actin regulator when mutated results in SCID through inhibition of thymic egress of mature thymocytes into peripheral lymphoid organs.

name: reticular dysgenesis
descr: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the most severe form of SCID and has_material_basis_in mutations in the gene encoding mitochondrial adenylate kinase 2. It is characterized by congenital agranulocytosis, lymphopenia, and lymphoid and thymic hypoplasia with absent cellular and humoral immunity functions.

name: DNA ligase IV deficiency
descr: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the LIG4 gene, a DNA ligase, encoding a protein essential for V(D)J recombination and DNA double-strand break (DSB) repair through nonhomologous end joining (NHEJ). Patients present with immunodeficiency and developmental and growth delay.

name: CD40 ligand deficiency
descr: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that is a X-linked immunodeficiency with hyperimmunoglobulin M (XHIM) affecting isotype switching and is caused by the absence of CD40 ligand which is normally expressed on activated CD4+ T cells. Individuals with this mutation are unable to switch from IgM to IgG, IgA and IgE.

name: immunodeficiency with hyper IgM type 3
descr: A hyper IgM syndrome that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TNFRSF5 gene, resulting in type 3 hyper-IgM immunodeficiency that is characterized by an inability of B cells to undergo isotype switching, an inability to mount an antibody-specific immune response, and a lack of germinal center formation.

name: lambda 5 deficiency
descr: A B cell deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutations in the IGLL1 gene. Lambda 5 mutations can cause a block in B cell development at the transition between the pro-B cell and the pre-B cell stage.

name: immunoglobulin alpha deficiency
descr: A B cell deficiency that is an autosomal recessive disorder that has_material_basis_in mutation in the IgA (CD79 alpha) antigen receptor.

name: immunoglobulin beta deficiency
descr: A B cell deficiency that is characterized by mucosal infections and autoimmune diseases due to lack of production of immunoglobulin A antibody, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: agammaglobulinemia 4
descr: An agammaglobulinemia that has_material_basis_in a mutation a homozygous mutation in the BLNK gene on chromosome 10q23.2.

name: Good syndrome
descr: An agammaglobulinemia that is a condition where there is co-occurrence of deficient cell-mediated immunity and benign thymoma.

name: autoimmune disease of exocrine system
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the exocrine system.

name: autoimmune disease of eyes, ear, nose and throat
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease located_in eyes, located_in ears, located_in nose and located_in throat.

name: autoimmune disease of gastrointestinal tract
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the gastrointestinal tract.

name: autoimmune disease of musculoskeletal system
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the musculoskeletal system.

name: autoimmune disease of peripheral nervous system
descr: An autoimmune disease of the nervous system that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the peripheral nervous system.

name: intrinsic cardiomyopathy
descr: A cardiomyopathy that is characterized as weakness in the muscle of the heart that is not due to an identifiable external cause.

name: developmental disorder of mental health
descr: A disease of mental health that occur during a child's developmental period between birth and age 18 resulting in retarding of the child's psychological or physical development.

name: specific developmental disorder
descr: A developmental disorder of mental health that categorizes specific learning disabilities and developmental disorders affecting coordination.

name: autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue
