descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the skin and connective tissue.

name: pervasive developmental disorder
descr: A developmental disorder of mental health that refers to a group of five disorders characterized by impairments in socialization and communication, as well as restricted interests and repetitive behaviors.

name: autism spectrum disorder
descr: A pervasive developmental disorder that is a spectrum of psychological conditions. The disease has_symptom widespread abnormalities of social interactions and communication, has_symptom severely restricted interests and has_symptom highly repetitive behavior.

name: atypical autism
descr: An autism spectrum disorder that involves some autistic symptoms occuring after age 3 with an abscence of all the traits necessary for a diagnosis of autism.

name: sexual disorder
descr: A disease of mental health that involves the impairment in normal sexual functioning.

name: paraphilia disorder
descr: A sexual disorder that is characterized recurrent, intense sexually arousing fantasies, sexual urges or behaviors generally involving nonhuman objects.

name: Munchausen by proxy
descr: A factitious disorder that involves a care giver's deliberate exaggeration, fabrication, and/or induce physical, psychological, behavioral, and/or mental health problems in others.

name: aphasia
descr: A language disorder that involves an acquired impairment of any laguage modality such as producting or comprehending spoken or written language.

name: writing disorder
descr: A learning disability that involves impaired written language ability such as impairments in handwriting, spelling, organization of ideas, and composition.

name: nosophobia
descr: A specific phobia that involves an irrational fear of contracting a disease.

name: autoimmune disease of urogenital tract
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the urogenital tract.

name: autoimmune disease of blood
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the blood.

name: autoimmune disease of cardiovascular system
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the cardiovascular system.

name: autonomic peripheral neuropathy
descr: A neuropathy that affects the autonomic nervous system and is characterized by urinary incontinence, gastrointestinal dysmotility, orthostatic hypotension, apneas, sweat disturbances and impotence.

name: popliteal pterygium syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by abnormal development of the face, skin and genitals. Clinical expressions of the disease include cleft lip, with or without cleft palate, contractures of the lower extremities, abnormal external genitalia, syndactyly of fingers and/or toes, and a pyramidal skin fold over the hallux nail. It has_material_basis_in mutations in the IRF6 gene on chromosome 1.

name: hypersensitivity reaction disease
descr: An immune system disease that has_material_basis_in abnormal immune responses.

name: gluten allergy
descr: A food allergy to wheat that is characterized by stomach cramping, diarrhea and gastrointestinal upset and is unrelated to the gluten intolerance.

name: lymphoma
descr: A hematologic cancer that affects lymphocytes that reside in the lymphatic system and in blood-forming organs.

name: non-Hodgkin lymphoma
descr: A lymphoma that is characterized as any kind of lymphoma except Hodgkin's lymphoma.

name: cutaneous T cell lymphoma
descr: A non-Hodgkin's lymphoma that has_material_basis_in a mutation of T cells.

name: familial juvenile hyperuricemic nephropathy
descr: A kidney disease that is characterized by hyperuricemia with renal uric acid under-excretion, gout and chronic kidney disease.

name: sideroblastic anemia 1
descr: A sideoblastic anemia that is characterized by the presence of microcytic hypochromic anemia and iron overload, and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance of mutation in the ALAS2 gene that enocdes aminolevulinic acid synthase that catalyzes the first step in heme production.

name: autosomal recessive pyridoxine-refractory sideroblastic anemia 2
descr: A sideroblastic anemia that is characterized by microcytic hypochromic anemia and iron overload, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the SLC25A38 gene.

name: pyridoxine-responsive sideroblastic anemia
descr: A sideoblastic anemia that is characterized by the presence of microcytic hypochromic anemia and iron overload, and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance.

name: Pearson syndrome
descr: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by sideroblastic anemia and exocrine pancreas dysfunction.

name: marantic endocarditis
descr: An endocarditis that results from the deposition of small sterile vegetations on valve leaflets.

name: pre-malignant neoplasm
descr: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body, which do not invade or destroy the surrounding tissue but, given enough time, will transform into a cancer.

name: benign neoplasm
descr: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body which lack the ability to metastasize.

name: lymphatic system cancer
descr: An immune system cancer that is located_in the lymphatic system and is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of lymphoid tissue.

name: ductal carcinoma in situ
descr: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by being non-invasive, not having spread outside of the duct into the surrounding breast tissue, has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells, derives_from epithelial cells.

name: estrogen-receptor positive breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of estrogen receptors.

name: estrogen-receptor negative breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of estrogen receptors.

name: progesterone-receptor positive breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of progesterone receptors.

name: progesterone-receptor negative breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of progesterone receptors.

name: Her2-receptor positive breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of Her2 receptors.

name: Her2-receptor negative breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of Her2 receptors.

name: triple-receptor negative breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of estrogen, progresterone and Her2 receptors.

name: breast benign neoplasm
descr: A thoracic benign neoplasm that is characterized by lack of malignancy.

name: immune system cancer
descr: An organ system cancer located_in the immune system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation in organs of the immune system.

name: cell type benign neoplasm
descr: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the type of cell or tissue from which it is derived.

name: organ system benign neoplasm
descr: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the organ system from which it is arising from.

name: female reproductive organ benign neoplasm
descr: A reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is characterized by a lack of malignancy located_in the female reproductive system.

name: male reproductive organ benign neoplasm
descr: A reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is characterized by a lack of malignancy located_in the male reproductive system.

name: vestibular gland benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vestibular gland.

name: endocrine organ benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in endocrine glands which secretes a type of hormone directly into the bloodstream to regulate the body.

name: central nervous system benign neoplasm
descr: A central nervous system benign neoplasm that is characterized by lack of malignancy.

name: cardiovascular organ benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm disease located_in the blood, heart, blood vessels or the lymphatic system.

name: immune system organ benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the immune system organs.

name: bone benign neoplasm
descr: A connective tissue benign neoplasm that is located_in bone.

name: uterine benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the uterus.

name: sensory organ benign neoplasm
descr: A nervous system benign neoplasm that is located_in a sensory organ.

name: thoracic benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplam that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

name: osteoblastoma
descr: A bone benign neoplasm of the bone that is characterized by clinical and histological similarity to osteoid osteomas.

name: musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the muscular and skeletal organs.

name: musculoskeletal system cancer
descr: An organ system cancer located_in the muscular and skeletal organs and characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of the musculoskeletal organs.

name: benign glioma
descr: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

name: cartilage cancer
descr: A connective tissue tumor that can be a benign chondroma or a maligannt chondrosarcoma.

name: central nervous system primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm
descr: A central nervous system cancer of children and young adults that develops from neural crest cells located_in cerebrum, has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from neuroectoderm.

name: cerebellar medulloblastoma
descr: A cerebellum cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

name: brain meningioma
descr: A brain cancer that is characterized by tumor of the meninges, that develops from the membranes that surround the brain and spinal cord, has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from meningeal cells of embryonic ectoderm origin.

name: brain glioma
descr: A brain cancer that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

name: vulvar benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vulva.

name: cervical benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the cervix.

name: fallopian tube benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the fallopian tube.

name: ovarian benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the ovary.

name: vaginal benign neoplasm
descr: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vagina.

name: nervous system benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.

name: sensory system cancer
descr: A nervous system cancer that is located in the sensory system.

name: peritoneal benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the serous membrane lining the abdominal cavity or coelom.

name: thoracic disease
descr: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

name: pharynx cancer
descr: A gastrointestinal system cancer that is located_in the pharynx.

name: integumentary system benign neoplasm
descr: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the integumentary system organs.

name: integumentary system cancer
descr: An organ system cancer that is located_in the skin, hair and nails.

name: connective tissue benign neoplasm
descr: A musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm that is located_in connective tissue.

name: heavy chain disease
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type IV disease that results from a proliferation of cells producing immunoglobulin heavy chains.

name: alpha chain disease
descr: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of alpha antibodies (IgA).

name: gamma heavy chain disease
descr: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of gamma antibody (IgG).

name: mu chain disease
descr: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of mu antibody (IgM).

name: delta chain disease
descr: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of delta antibody (IgD).

name: akinetopsia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of motion perception.

name: alexithymia
descr: An agnosia that is a deficiency in understanding, processing, or describing emotions.

name: amusia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize musical notes, rhythms, and intervals.

name: anosognosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to gain feedback about one's own condition or impairments.

name: apperceptive agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish visual shapes.

name: apraxia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to map out physical actions in order to repeat them in functional activities.

name: associative agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize visual scenes or classes of objects but retain the abilty to describe them.

name: auditory agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguishing environmental and non-verbal auditory cues including difficulty distinguishing speech from non-speech sounds even though hearing is usually normal.

name: autotopagnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to orient parts of the body.

name: color agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize a color, while being able to perceive or distinguish it.

name: cortical deafness
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive any auditory information but whose hearing is intact.

name: finger agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish the fingers on the hand.

name: form agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive a whole object while perceiving only parts of details.

name: integrative agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to integrate these elements together into comprehensible perceptual wholes while recognizing elements of the whole.

name: mirror agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to acknowledge objects in the neglected field that are visible when a mirror reflects the object visible in the non-neglected field.

name: pain agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive and process pain.

name: phonagnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize familiar voices.

name: semantic agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognise an object while maintaining the use of non-visual sensory systems such as feeling, tapping, smelling, rocking or flicking the object to recognise the object.

name: simultanagnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recgonize a whole image or scene while retianing the ability to recognize objects or details in their visual field one at a time.

name: social emotional agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive facial expression, body language and intonation, rendering them unable to non-verbally perceive people's emotions and limiting that aspect of social interaction.

name: astereognosia
descr: An agnosia that is the loss of the ability to recognize objects by touch based on its texture, size and weight.

name: tactile agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize or identify objects by touch alone.

name: time agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehend the succession and duration of events.

name: topographical agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to rely on visual cues to guide them directionally due to the inability to recognise objects.

name: verbal auditory agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognising spoken words as semantically meaningful.

name: visual agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognize objects.

name: visual verbal agnosia
descr: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehending the meaning of written words.

name: diffuse alopecia areata
descr: An alopecia areata that involves diffuse loss of hair over the whole scalp.

name: acquired metabolic disease
descr: A disease of metabolism that has _material_basis_in enzyme deficiency or accumulation of enzymes or toxins which interfere with normal function due to an endocrine organ disease, organ malfunction, inadequate intake, dietary deficiency, or malabsorption.

name: organic acidemia
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that disrupts normal amino acid metabolism causing a building up of branched-chain amino acids.

name: survival motor neuron spinal muscular atrophy
descr: A spinal muscular atrophy that is associated with the survival of motor neuron protein.

name: Kennedy's disease
descr: A spinal muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in an X-linked recessive expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) in exon 1 of AR gene encoding the androgen receptor.

name: dentatorubral-pallidoluysian atrophy
descr: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that has_material_basis_in expansion of  CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) encoding a polyglutamine tract in the atrophin-1 protein.

name: body dysmorphic disorder
descr: A somatoform disorder that involves an excessive concern about and preoccupation with a perceived defect in his or her physical features (body image).

name: pain disorder
descr: A somatoform disorder that involves chronic pain in one or more areas, and is thought to be caused by psychological stress.

name: Kleine-Levin syndrome
descr: A recurrent hypersomnia that is characterized by recurring periods of excessive amounts of sleep and altered behavior.

name: bipolar ll disorder
descr: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one hypomanic episode and at least one major depressive episode; with this disorder, depressive episodes are more frequent and more intense than manic episodes.

name: seasonal affective disorder
descr: A mental depression that involves presentation of depressive symptoms only during a specific season of the year.

name: histidinemia
descr: A histidine metabolism disease characterized by a deficiency of the enzyme histidase.

name: benign familial infantile epilepsy
descr: An infancy electroclinical syndrome that is characterized by convulsions, with onset at age 3 to 12 months.

name: generalized epilepsy with febrile seizures plus
descr: An idiopathic generalized epilepsy that is characterized by febrile seizures often with accessory afebrile generalized tonic-clonic seizures with childhood onset.

name: juvenile absence epilepsy
descr: An adolescence-adult electroclinical syndrome statring between the age of ten to 17 years characterized by the occurrence of typical absence seizures.

name: Timothy syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by cardiac, hand/foot, facial, and neurodevelopmental features. The two forms are type 1 (classic) and type 2, a rare form that has_material_basis_in mutations in a transcript variant of CACNA1C on chromosome 12p13.33.

name: GABA aminotransferase deficiency
descr: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a defect in the gene coding for gamma-aminobutyrate transaminase, which is responsible for catabolism of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), an important, mostly inhibitory neurotransmitter in the central nervous system, into succinic semialdehyde.

name: succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase deficiency
descr: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a deficiency of succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase resulting in elevated levels of gamma-hydroxybutyric acid.

name: gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by impairment of the GABA catabolic pathway.

name: homocarnosinosis
descr: A gamma-amino butyric acid metabolism disorder that is characterized by an excess of homocarnosine in the brain and has_material_basis_in a deficiency of serum carnosinase in its ability to hydrolyze homocarnosine.

name: familial hemiplegic migraine
descr: A migraine with aura that is characterized by temporary numbness or weakness, often affecting one side of the body (hemiparesis). Additional features of an aura can include difficulty with speech, confusion, and drowsiness.

name: Renpenning syndrome
descr: An intellectual disability that is characterized by small head size (microcephaly), long narrow face, short stature, small testes, and intellectual deficit which follows X-linked inheritance and presents most often in males.

name: colitis
descr: An inflammatory bowel disease that involves inflammation located_in colon.

name: ischemic colitis
descr: A colitis caused_by inadequate blood supply to the colon.

name: microscopic colitis
descr: A colitis that can only be diagnosed_by the examination of colon tissue under a microscope.

name: collagenous colitis
descr: A colitis characterized by a distinctive thickening of the subepithelial collagen table.

name: lymphocytic colitis
descr: A colitis characterized by an accumulation of lymphocytes in the colonic epithelium and connective tissue (lamina propria).

name: Clostridium difficile colitis
descr: A colitis characterized by an overgrowth of Clostridium difficile bacteria.

name: chemical colitis
descr: A colitis caused_by introduction of various chemicals.

name: diversion colitis
descr: A colitis caused_by diversion of the fecal stream due to complication of ileostomy or colostomy.

name: jejunoileitis
descr: An inflammatory bowel disease that is characterized by patchy areas of inflammation located_in jejunum, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom cramps and has_symptom formation of fistulas.

name: ileitis
descr: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in ileum, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom abdominal pain, often in the right lower quadrant, has_symptom weight loss.

name: ileocolitis
descr: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in colon and located_in ileum, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom abdominal pain in middle or lower right part.

name: gastroduodenal Crohn's disease
descr: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in stomach and located_in duodenum, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom weight loss and has_symptom loss of appetite.

name: Crohn's colitis
descr: An inflammatory bowel disease characterized by inflammation located_in colon only, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom rectal bleeding, has_symptom skin lesions and has_symptom formation of ulcers, fistulas and abscesses around the anus.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 1
descr: The most common type of familial ALS that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SOD1 gene on chromosome 21.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 2
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the alsin gene on chromosome 2.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 3
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in loci on chromosome 18.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 4
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with juvenile onset that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SETX gene on chromosome 9.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 5
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SPG11 gene on chromosome 15q21.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 6
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FUS gene on chromosome 16.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 7
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in loci on chromosome 20.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 9
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ANG gene on chromosome 14.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 10
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TARDBP gene on chromosome 1.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 11
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FIG4 gene on chromosome 6.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 12
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the OPTN gene on chromosome 10.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 13
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis where a mutation that has_material_basis_in the ATXN2 gene on chromosome 12 contributes to suscepitbility.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 14
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the VCP gene on chromosome 9.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 15
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the UBQLN2 gene on chromosome X.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 16
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SIGMAR1 gene (SETX) on chromosome 9.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 17
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CHMP2B gene on chromosome 3.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 18
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the PFN1 gene on chromosome 17.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 19
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ERBB4 gene on chromosome 2.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 20
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with juvenile onset that has_material_basis_in mutation in the HNRNPA1 gene on chromosome 12.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 21
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the MATR3 gene on chromosome 5.

name: FTDALS1
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the C9ORF72 gene on chromosome 9. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.

name: FTDALS2
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CHCHD10 gene on chromosome 22. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.

name: Balo concentric sclerosis
descr: A demyelinating disease characterized by the fact that the demyelinated tissues form concentric layers.

name: Cogan syndrome
descr: An eye disease characterized by nonsyphilitic interstitial keratitis located_in cornea, has_symptom fever, has_symptom fatigue.

name: Cogan-Reese syndrome
descr: An eye disease characterized by variable iris atrophy, pigmented and pedunculated nodules located_in iris and attachment of the iris to the cornea (peripheral anterior synechiae) and characterized_by glaucoma.

name: CREST syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by calcinosis, Raynaud's phenomeno, esophageal dysmotility, sclerodactyly and telangiectasia.

name: lymph node adenoid cystic carcinoma
descr: A lymph node cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures of the lymph nodes. These structures are typically filled with a mucous-like material or contain abnormal fibrous membranes.

name: physical urticaria
descr: An urticaria induced by external physical influences.

name: Maffucci syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by the presence of multiple enchondromas (benign growths of cartilage) associated with multiple hemangiomas.

name: Scheie syndrome
descr: A mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by corneal clouding, facial dysmorphism and normal lifespan.

name: agraphia
descr: An acquired writing disorder causing a loss in the ability to communicate through writing, either due to some motor dysfunction or the inability to spell.

name: atrial fibrillation
descr: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by uncoordinated electrical activity in the heart's upper chambers (the atria), which causes the heartbeat to become fast and irregular and has symptoms palpitations, weakness, fatigue, lightheadedness, dizziness, confusion, shortness of breath and chest pain.

name: 3MC syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by blepharophimosis, blepharoptosis, highly arched eyebrows hypertelorism, cleft lip and palate, postnatal growth deficiency, cognitive impairment, hearing loss and, in a smaller percentage of cases, craniosynostosis, radioulnar synostosis and genital and vesicorenal anomalies. It encompasses four disorders that were previously designated the Malpuech, Michels, Mingarelli and Carnevale syndromes.

name: acrofrontofacionasal dysostosis

name: Adams-Oliver syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by defects of the scalp (aplasia cutis congenita), abnormalities of the fingers, toes, arms and legs.

name: intracranial berry aneurysm
descr: An intracranial aneurysm with a characteristic rounded shape; the most common form of cerebral aneurysm.

name: Baraitser-Winter syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by distinctive facial features including hypertelorism, large eyelid openings, ptosis, high-arched eyebrows, a broad nasal bridge and tip of the nose, a long space between the nose and the upper lip, full cheeks and a pointed chin; structural abnormalities of the brain might also be present.

name: basal ganglia calcification
descr: A basal ganglia disease characterized by the presence of abnormal calcium deposits of unknown cause in the brain; has symptom dementia, psychosis, mood swings and loss of acquired motor skills.

name: Bruck syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by a combination of multiple joint contractures and osteogenesis imperfecta.

name: branchiootic syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by malformations of the outer, middle and inner ear and branchial and renal malformations. Mutations of the EYA1, SIX1 and SIX5 genes are associated with the syndrome.

name: cardiofaciocutaneous syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by unusually sparse, brittle, curly hair, macrocephaly, a prominent forehead and bi-temporal narrowing, intellectual disability, failure to thrive, congenital heart defects, short stature and skin abnormalities, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the BRAF, MAP2K1, MAP2kK2 and KRAS genes.

name: Carpenter syndrome
descr: An acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by craniosynostosis, acrocephaly, obesity, syndactyly and polydactyly.

name: carnitine palmitoyltransferase II deficiency
descr: A lipid metabolism disorder characterized by an enzymatic defect that prevents long-chain fatty acids from being transported into the mitochondria.

name: xanthinuria
descr: A purine-pyrimidine metabolic disorder characterized by deficiency of xanthine oxidase, resulting in excretion of large amounts of xanthine in the urine and the formation of xanthine stones.

name: Warburg micro syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by severe intellectual disability, microcephaly, congenital cataract, microcornea, microphthalmia, agenesis or hypoplasia of the corpus callosum and hypogenitalism.

name: Van Maldergem syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by facial abnormalities such as telecanthus, epicanthus, broad flattened nose, large inverted W-shaped mouth and malformed ears, malformed extremities such as camptodactyly, clinodactyly, interdigital webbing and joint hyperlaxity and mental retardation.

name: Van der Woude syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by the combination of lower lip pits, cleft lip with or without cleft palate and cleft palate alone.

name: UV-sensitive syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by photosensitivity and liver spots (solar lentigines).

name: 3-M syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by dwarfism, facial dysmorphia and skeletal abnormalities.

name: synpolydactyly
descr: A syndactyly characterized by an increased number of digits; often a result of a mutation in the HOX D13 gene.

name: stuttering
descr: An articulation disorder characterized by involuntary sound repetition and disruption or blocking of speech.

name: specific language impairment
descr: A language disorder characterized by difficulty in language acquisition despite otherwise normal development and in the absence of any obvious explanatory factors.

name: Mast syndrome
descr: A hereditary spastic paraplegia associated with dementia.

name: MASA syndrome
descr: A hereditary spastic paraplegia that is characterized by hydrocephalus, spasticity of the lower limbs, adducted thumbs, aphasia, seizures, agenesis of the corpus callosum and intellectual disability in the mild to moderate range.

name: Smith-McCort dysplasia
descr: A Syggve-Melchior-Clausen disease characterized by short limbs and a short trunk with a barrel-shaped chest and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DYM gene on chromosome 18q.

name: Simpson-Golabi-Behmel syndrome type 1
descr: An X-linked recessive disease characterized by pre- and postnatal overgrowth and craniofacial, skeletal, cardiac and renal abnormalities and has_material_basis_in mutation in the gene encoding glypican-3 on chromosome Xq26.

name: scoliosis
descr: A bone structure disease characterized by an appreciable lateral deviation in the normally straight vertical line of the spine.

name: idiopathic scoliosis
descr: A scoliosis with no known cause.

name: sclerosteosis
descr: A hyperostosis characterized by excessive bone formation most prominent in the skull, mandible, clavicle, ribs and diaphyses of long bones; bone formation occurs throughout life.

name: sclerocornea
descr: A corneal disease in which the cornea blends with sclera, resulting in clouding of the cornea.

name: scapuloperoneal myopathy
descr: A muscular dystrophy which begins at the lower legs and affects the shoulder region earlier and more severely than distal arm.

name: Robinow syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by mild to moderate short stature due to growth delays after birth, distinctive craniofacial abnormalities, skeletal malformations and genital abnormalities.

name: rippling muscle disease 2
descr: A muscle tissue disease characterized by mechanically triggered contractions of skeletal muscle and that has_material_basis_in mutation in the caveolin-3 gene (CAV3) on chromosome 3p25.

name: Dowling-Degos disease
descr: A pigmentation disease characterized by a reticulate pattern of abnormally dark skin coloring, particularly in the body's folds and creases.

name: dyschromatosis symmetrica hereditaria
descr: A pigmentation disease characterized by progressively pigmented and depigmented macules, often mixed in a reticulate pattern, concentrated on the dorsal extremities.

name: reticulate acropigmentation of Kitamura
descr: A pigmentation disease characterized by lesions that initially arise as letiginous, hyperpigmented macules in a reticular pattern on the dorsal aspect of the hands and feet. Over time, lesions may spread proximally and may darken; palmoplantar pitting and dermatoglyphic disruption may also be present.

name: renal-hepatic-pancreatic dysplasia
descr: A physical disorder characterized by pancreatic fibrosis, renal dysplasia and hepatic dysgenesis; it is usual fatal soon after birth.

name: ptosis
descr: An eye disease characterized by the drooping or falling of the upper or lower eyelid.

name: congenital ptosis
descr: A ptosis characterized by eyelid drop present at birth.

name: gallbladder disease
descr: A gastrointestinal system disease that is located_in the gallbladder.

name: porencephaly
descr: A brain disease that is characterized by encephalomalacia and cystic brain lesions.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia
descr: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by underdevelopment of the pons and cerebellum.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 1A
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by central and peripheral motor dysfunction, hypotonia, spasticity and failure to thrive, has_material_basis_in mutation in the VRK1 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 1B
descr: A severe pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by hypotonia, progressive microcephaly and developmental delay, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the EXOSC3 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 2A
descr: A severe pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, chorea, epilepsy and hyperreflexia, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the TSEN54 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 2B
descr: A severe pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, clonus, dysphagia and failure to thrive, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the TSEN2 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 2C
descr: A severe pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, extrapyramidal dyskinesia, seizure and failure to thrive, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the TSEN34 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 2D
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, profound intellectual disability, spasticity and seizure, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the SEPSECS gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 2E
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, profound intellectual disability, spasticity and seizure, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the VPS53 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 3
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, hypotonia, dysmorphic features, profound intellectual disability and seizure, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the PCLO gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 4
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, hypertonia, myoclonus, seizure and early lethality, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the TSEN54 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 5
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by severe olivopontocerebellar hypoplasia and degeneration leading to early lethality, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the TSEN54 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 6
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by olivopontocerebellar hypoplasia and developmental delay, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the RARS2 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 7
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by delayed psychomotor development, hypotonia, gonadal abnormalities and respiratory failure, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive mutation in the TOE1 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 8
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by delayed psychomotor development, chorea, hypotonia, spasticity and visual defects, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the CHMP1A gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 9
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by progressive microcephaly, spasticity, seizure and brain atrophy, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the AMPD2 gene.

name: pontocerebellar hypoplasia type 10
descr: A pontocerebellar hypoplasia that is characterized by severe developmental delays, progressive microcephaly, spasticity and seizure, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the CLP1 gene.

name: primary pigmented nodular adrenocortical disease
descr: An adrenal cortex disease characterized by small to normal sized adrenal glands containing multiple small cortical pigmented nodules.

name: photosensitive epilepsy
descr: An epilepsy characterized by seizures triggered by visual stimuli that form patterns in space or time, such as flashing lights.

name: persistent hyperplastic primary vitreous
descr: A developmental vitreous disease that is characterized by leukocoria, strabismus and vision loss, caused by failure of primary vitreous and hyaloid vasculature to regress during embryological development.

name: peeling skin syndrome
descr: A skin disease that is characterized by the painless peeling of the top layer of skin predominately on the hands and feet, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the TGM5 gene and/pr CSTA gene.

name: paroxysmal nocturnal hemoglobinuria
descr: An aquired hemolytic anemia that is characterized by abdominal pain, hematuria, esophageal dysmotility and thrombosis, has_material_basis_in defect in the cell membrane glycosyl phosphatidylinositols that protect red blood cells from the innate complement immune system.

name: parietal foramina
descr: An inherited neural tube defect that is characterized by enlarged openings in the parietal bones of the skull, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ALX4 gene or MSX2 gene.

name: combined oxidative phosphorylation deficiency
descr: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by growth retardation, microcephaly, hypertonia, encephalopathy, cardiomyopathy and liver dysfunction, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: cornea plana
descr: A corneal disease that is characterized by a flat cornea where the radus of curvature is less than 43 D.

name: omodysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by severe congenital shortening and distal tapering of the humeri and femori as well as cryptorchidism, congential heart defects, cognitive delay and dysmorphic facies, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the GPC6 gene.

name: Ohdo syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis, dental hypoplasia, hearing impairment and intellectual disability.

name: blepharophimosis-intellectual disability syndrome, SBBYS type
descr: A Ohdo syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis and intellectual disability.

name: oculodentodigital dysplasia
descr: A syndrome characterized by craniofacial, neurologic, limb and ocular abnormalities.

name: X-linked chondrodysplasia punctata 1
descr: A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by maxillary hypoplasia, stippled chondrodystrophy, flat nasal tip and short columella, has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive inheritance, has_material_basis_in deficiency of arylsulfatase E. and is associated with associated with vitamin K-related teratogenicity.

name: autosomal dominant chondrodysplasia punctata
descr: A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by abnormal facies and stippling of the limbs, associated with vitamin K-related teratogenicity, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: cold-induced sweating syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by profuse sweating induced by cold ambient temperature.

name: complement component 2 deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the C2 gene.

name: congenital secretory chloride diarrhea 1
descr: A secretory diarrhea that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SLC26A3 gene.

name: complement component 4a deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrnet bascterial infections, caused by C4A deficiency.

name: complement component 4b deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrnet bascterial infections, caused by C4B deficiency.

name: complement component 6 deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrnet bascterial infections, has_material_basis_in mutation in the C6 gene.

name: complement component 7 deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized byrecurrnet bascterial infections, has_material_basis_in mutation in the C7 gene.

name: type I complement component 8 deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by deficiency of the alpha subunit of complement protein 8, which causes increased susceptibility to recurrent bacterial infections, especially to Neisseria meningitidis, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the C8A gene, which produces the alpha subunit of complement component 8 important in forming membrane attack complexes.

name: type II complement component 8 deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by deficiency of the beta subunit of complement protein 8, which causes increased susceptibility to recurrent bacterial infections, especially to Neisseria meningitidis, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the C8B gene, which produces the beta subunit of complement component 8 important in forming membrane attack complexes.

name: complement component 9 deficiency
descr: A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrnet bascterial infections, has_material_basis_in mutation in the C9 gene.

name: dyschromatosis universalis hereditaria
descr: A pigmentation disease characterized by reticulate hyper- and hypo-pigmentated macules in a generalized distribution.

name: megalocornea
descr: A corneal disease that is characterized by a bilaterally enlarged corneal diameter without an increase in intraocular pressure and that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CHRDL1 gene.

name: Meier-Gorlin syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by bilateral underdevelopment of the external ear, short stature, absent or underdeveloped patellae and severe prenatal and postnatal growth retardation.

name: autosomal dominant non-syndromic intellectual disability
descr: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

name: autosomal recessive non-syndromic intellectual disability
descr: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

name: syndromic X-linked intellectual disability
descr: A syndromic intellectual characterized by an X-linked inheritance pattern.

name: uvulitis
descr: An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the swelling of the uvula to 3-5 times its normal size.

name: adenoid hypertrophy
descr: An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the unusual growth of the adenoid tonsil; has symptom snoring, has symptom hyponasality, has symptom otitis media with effusion, has symptom mouth breathing.

name: angular cheilitis
descr: A cheilitis characterized by inflammation of one or both of the corners of the mouth.

name: tracheomalacia
descr: A tracheal disease characterized by flaccidity of the tracheal support cartilage.

name: persistent generalized lymphadenopathy
descr: A lymph node disease characterized by enlarged, non-painful lymph nodes occurring for more than three to six months for which no other reason can be found.

name: oral hairy leukoplakia
descr: A mouth disease characterized by a white patch on the side of the tongue with a corrugated or hairy appearance; caused by Epstein-Barr virus.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome I
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by malformations of the face, oral cavity, and digits, has_material_basis_in X-linked dominant inheritance of the OFD1 gene with lethality in males and is associated with polycystic kidney disease.

name: lung abscess
descr: A lung disease characterized by microbial infection which causes a type of liquefactive necrosis of the pulmonary tissue and formation of cavities containing necrotic debris or fluid.

name: acute promyelocytic leukemia
descr: An acute myeloid leukemia characterized by accumulation of promyelocytes in the bone marrow and by a translocation between chromosomes 15 and 17.

name: cardiac arrest
descr: A congestive heart failure characterized by a sudden stop in effective blood circulation due to the failure of the heart to contract effectively or at all.

name: inguinal hernia
descr: An intestinal disease characterized by a protrusion of abdominal cavity contests through the inguinal canal.

name: umbilical hernia
descr: A intestinal disease characterized by the protrusion by part of the intestine though an opening in the abdominal muscles.

name: mastoiditis
descr: A middle ear disease characterized by an inflammation of the mucosal lining of the mastoid antrum and the mastoid air cell system inside the mastoid process.

name: breast abscess
descr: A breast disease characterized by a collection of pus in the breast.

name: dental abscess
descr: A tooth disease characterized by a localized collection of pus associated with a tooth.

name: cervical polyp
descr: A cervix disease characterized by a benign polyp on the surface of the cervical canal.

name: myelomeningocele
descr: A spina bifida characterized by protrusion of the spinal cord through an opening, covered by meningeal membranes.

name: omphalocele
descr: A physical disorder characterized by a defect in the development of the abdominal wall muscles, resulting in the intestines, liver and other organs to remain outside of the abdomen in a sac.

name: anal fistula
descr: An anus disease characterized by is an abnormal connection between the epithelialised surface of the anal canal and the perianal skin.

name: ectopic pregnancy
descr: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the implantation of the embryo outside the uterine cavity.

name: Rapp-Hodgkin syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by abnormal development of ectodermal tissues including the skin, hair, nails, teeth and sweat glands and anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with cleft lip/palate.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 2
descr: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TMEM70 gene on chromosome 8q21.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 3
descr: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATP5E gene on chromosome 20q13.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 4
descr: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATP5A1 gene on chromosome 18q.

name: transient neonatal diabetes mellitus
descr: A neonatal diabetes mellitus characterized by hyperglycemia during the neonatal period that remits during infancy but recurs in later life in most patients.

name: autosomal dominant sideroblastic anemia 4
descr: A sideroblastic anemia characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria
descr: An organic acidemia that is characterized by elevated levels of 3-methylglutaconic acid and 3-methylglutaric acid in the urine.

name: CEDNIK syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the SNAP29 gene and characterized by a unique constellation of clinical manifestations including microcephaly, severe neurologic impairment, psychomotor retardation, failure to thrive, facial dysmoprhism, palmoplantar keratoderma and late-onset ichthyosis.

name: parameningeal embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma
descr: An embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma located in the parameningeal region.

name: chronic atrial and intestinal dysrhythmia
descr: A syndrome characterized by a unique combination of cardiac arrhythmias and intestinal pseudo-obstruction. It has_material_basis_in the mutated SGOL1 protein. Distinctive clinical features include atrial dysrhythmias, sick sinus syndrome (SSS) and valve anomalies and chronic intestinal pseudo-obstruction (CIPO).

name: ciliopathy
descr: A syndrome associated with mutations encoding defective proteins, which result in either abnormal function formation or function of cilia.

name: agnathia-otocephaly complex
descr: A physical disorder characterized by mandibular hypoplasia or agnathia, ventromedial auricular malposition (melotia) and/or auricular fusion (synotia), and microstomia with oroglossal hypoplasia or aglossia. Holoprosencephaly is the most commonly identified association, but skeletal, genitourinary and cardiovascular anomalies and situs inversus have been reported.

name: acromelic frontonasal dysostosis
descr: A dysostosis characterized by cranium bifidum, severe hypertelorism, median cleft lip and palate, nasal bifurcation, brachycephaly, large fontanelle, tibial hemimelia, preaxial polydactyly of the feet and brain malformations.

name: glucocorticoid-induced osteoporosis
descr: An osteoporosis caused by chronic glucocorticoid use. Glucocorticoids impair the replication, differentiation and function of osteoblasts and induce the apoptosis of mature osteoblasts and osteocytes; the also favor osteoclastogenesis leading to an increase in bone resorption.

name: acrodermatitis chronica atrophicans
descr: An acrodermatitis characterized by a chronically progressive course, leading to widespread atrophy of the skin. It is a clinical manifestation of Lyme borreliosis.

name: bacillary angiomatosis
descr: A bartonellosis that has_material_basis_in Bartonella henselae or has_material_basis_in Bartonella quintana. The disease is characterized by the proliferation of blood vessels, resulting in them forming tumour-like masses in the skin and other organs.

name: Native American myopathy
descr: A neuromuscular disease characterized by congenital weakness, arthrogryposis, cleft palate, ptosis, myopathic facies, short stature, kykphoscoliosis, talipes deformities and susceptibility to malignant hyperthermia provoked by anesthesia and that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the STAC3 gene on chromosome 12q13.

name: acrorenal syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by limb defects, usually bilateral, like cleft hands or feet and longitudinal defects involving radius or ulna, tibia or fibula and renal anomalies which include agenesis, hypoplasia and rarely polycystic kidneys. Additional malformations may involve the oro-mandibular region, the trachea and lungs, skin derivatives including sweat glands, mammary glands, the uterus, vas deferens, the nasal placodes and the eyes.

name: hypoparathyroidism-retardation-dysmorphism syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by permanent parathyroid hormone (PTH) deficiency, hypocalcemia, hyperphosphatemia, facial anomalies, and psychomotor retardation; it is seen among children born to consanguineous couple of Arab ethnicity.

name: microcephaly with or without chorioretinopathy, lymphedema, or mental retardation
descr: A syndrome characterized byvariable expression of microcephaly, ocular disorders including chorioretinopathy, congenital lymphedema of the lower limbs, and mild to moderate intellectual disability.

name: adenine phosphoribosyltransferase deficiency
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by the formation 2,8-dihydroxyadenine stones and renal failure secondary to intratubular crystalline precipitation. It has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 2
descr: A mitochondrial metabolism disease characterized by motor disability, with ataxia, apraxia, dystonia, and dysarthria, associated with necrotic lesions throughout the brain and has_material_basis_in mutation in the TTC19 gene on chromosome 17. It has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.

name: Kleefstra syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by childhood hypotonia, a distinctive facial appearance, speech impediments, developmental disability, epilepsy, congenital and urogenetic defects, microcephaly, corpulence, and psychiatric disorders and that has_material_basis_in a microdeletion in the chromosome region 9q34.3 or by a point mutation in the EHMT1 gene located in that region.

name: acrofacial dysostosis Cincinnati type
descr: An acrofacial dysostosis characterized by a spectrum of mandibulofacial dysostosis phenotypes, such as cleft palate, micrognathia, malar flattening, microcephaly and, in some cases, extrafacial skeletal defects. It is that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the POLR1A gene on chromosome 2p11.

name: Stormorken syndrome
descr: A blood platelet disease characterized by thrombocytopathy, thrombocytopenia, mild anemia, asplenia, tubular aggregate myopathy, miosis, headache, and ichthyosis. It has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the STM1 gene on chromosome 11p15. It has an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.

name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 22
descr: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TUBA4A gene on chromosome 2q35.

name: Vici syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by callosal agenesis, cataracts, cardiomyopathy, combined immunodeficiency and hypopigmentation. It has_material_basis_in mutation in the EPG5 gene on chromosome 18q12.3.

name: chylomicron retention disease
descr: A lipid metabolism disorder characterized by malnutrition, failure to thrive, growth failure, vitamin E deficiency and the absence of chylomicrons and apolipoprotein B48 post-prandially. It has an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern and has_material_basis_in mutations in the SAR1B gene on chromosome 5q31.1.

name: Sakati-Nyhan syndrome
descr: An acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by abnormalities in the bones of the legs, congenital heart defects and craniofacial defects and craniosynostosis. The patients suffer from cyanosis and other respiratory and breathing infections.

name: hereditary papulotranslucent acrokeratoderma
descr: A keratosis  of the hands and feet characterized by persistent, asymptomatic, yellowish to white papules and plaques associated with fine-textured scalp hair and an atopic diathesis.

name: punctate palmoplantar keratoderma
descr: A palmoplantar keratosis characterized by keratoses with a \

name: punctate palmoplantar keratoderma type III
descr: A punctate palmoplantar keratoderma that is characterized by hyperkeratinization of the palms and soles, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the AAGAB gene.

name: glycerol kinase deficiency
descr: An inherited metabolic disorder characterized_by wide range of phenotypic variability; patients can have severe metabolic and CNS abnormalities, while others possess hyperglycerolemia and glyceroluria with no other apparent phenotype and that has_material_basis_in mutation in the GK gene on chromosome Xp21.

name: Galloway-Mowat syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized_by is a rare autosomal recessive disease, characterized by microcephaly with brain anomalies including CA in some cases, intellectual disability, and early-infantile-onset nephrotic syndrome.

name: mandibulofacial dysostosis with alopecia
descr: A syndrome characterized by malar and mandibular hypoplasia, typically associated with abnormalities of the ears and eyelids, and with alopecia.

name: Hennekam syndrome
descr: A lymphatic system disease characterized by he presence of intestinal lymphangiectasia, mental retardation, and characteristic facial anomalies. It is inherited in an autosomal recessive pattern. Most individuals with Hennekam syndrome have characteristic facial abnormalities, such as a flat face with accompanying puffy eyelids and hypertelorism; the nasal bridge is typically flat and the ears are typically small. Congenital extremity and genital lymphedema is present in most patients.

name: Parkinson's disease 1
descr: A late onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in mutation in the alpha-synuclein gene on chromosome 4q22.1.

name: Parkinson's disease 2
descr: An early-onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in mutation in the parkin gene on chromosome 6q25.2-q27.

name: Parkinson's disease 6
descr: An early-onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in mutations in the PINK1 gene on chromosome 1p36.12.

name: Parkinson's disease 7
descr: An early-onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DJ1 gene on chromosome 1p36.

name: Parkinson's disease 8
descr: A late onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the dardarin encoding gene on chromosome 12q12.

name: Parkinson's disease 15
descr: An early-onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FBXO7 gene on chromosome 22q12.3.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome III
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by dysmorphic facies and severe intellectual deficits, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome IV
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by dysmorphic facies, the development of harmartomas of the tongue, polydactyly and limb dysplasia, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutations in the TCTN3 gene.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome V
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by postaxial polydactyly and median cleft of the upper lip and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the DDX59 gene on chromosome 1q32.

name: Joubert syndrome with orofaciodigital defect
descr: A Joubert syndrome that is characterized by orofaciodigital defect.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome VII
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by oral, facial and digital abnormalities, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome VIII
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by tongue lobulation, hypoplasia of the epiglottis, cleft lip, polydactyly, short stature and intellectual deficit, and has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive inheritance.

name: acrofacial dysostosis
descr: A hetergeneous dysostosis that is characterized by digital dysplasia, downslanted palpebral fissures, deafness and developmental delay, has_material_basis_in mutation to the SF3B4 gene.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome X
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by facial, oral and digital deformities as well as radial shortening, fibular agenesis and coalescence of tarsal bones.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome XI
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, bulbous nasal tip, broad nasal bridge, downslanting palpebral fissures, low set ears, skeletal malformations, intellectual deficits, deafness and congenital heart defects.

name: orofaciodigital syndrome IX
descr: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by highly arched palate with bifid tongue,  harmartomatous tongue, hypertelorism, telecanthus, strabismus,bifid nasal tip, short stature, bifid halluces, forked metatarsal, polydactyly, mild intellectual deficit and specific retinal abnormalities, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: acrofacial dysostosis Rodriguez type
descr: An acrofacial dysostosis that is characterized by CNS malformations, lung anomalies, congenital heart defects, dysmorphic facies and limb reduction, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: acrofacial dysostosis, Catania type
descr: An acrofacial dysostosis that is characterized by intrauterine growth retardation, short stature, microcephaly, cleft palate, limb hypoplasia, simian creases and cryptorchidism/hypospadias.

name: acrofacial dysostosis, Patagonia type
descr: An acrofacial dysostosis that is characterized by oligodontia, short stature, pili torti, syndactyly, vertebral abnormalities and cleft lip, and has_material_basis_in X-linked dominant inheritance.

name: Chilblain lupus
descr: A cutaneous form of systemic lupus erythermatosus that is characterized by painful nodular skin lesions precipitated by variation in temperatures, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the TREX1 gene.

name: chondrodysplasia Blomstrand type
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by rapid endochondral bone maturation, short limbs, dwarfism and prenatal lethality, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the PTH1R gene.

name: chromosomal deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal disease that has_material_basis_in partial deletion of chromosomes.

name: chromosome 10q23 deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal gene deletion syndrome that is characterized by dysmorphic facies, developmental delay and multiple congenital abnormalities and huvenile polyposis, has_material_basis_in recurrent deletions of chromosome 10q22.3-q23.2.

name: distal 10q deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by developmental delay, intellectual disability, behavioral problems and facial facies caused by a missing copy of the long arm of chromosome 10.

name: chromosome 13q14 deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by low birth weight, dysmorphic facies, limb defects, genital malformations and psychomotor developmental delay, has_material_basis_in deletion of the long arm of chromosome 13.

name: chromosome 14q11-q22 deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by microcephaly, dysmorphic facies, psychomotor delay and failure to thrive, has_material_basis_in isolated cases of partial deletion of the long arm of chromosome 14.

name: chromosome 15q11.2 deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by intellectual disbaility, dysmorphic facies, psychiatric illness and autism spectrum disorder, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of partial deletion of the long arm of chromosome 15.

name: chromosome 15q13.3 microdeletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by intellectual dsability, developmental delay, autism spectrum disorder and seizure, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of partial deletion of the long arm of chromosome 15.

name: chromosome 15q24 deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by dysmorphic facial features, intellectual disability and seizure, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the SIN3A gene causing partial deletion of the long arm of chromosome 15.

name: chromosome 15q25 deletion syndrome
descr: A chromosomal deletion syndrome that is characterized by intellectual disability and developmental delay, has_material_basis_in partial deletion of the long arm of chromosome 15.

name: Cole-Carpenter syndrome
descr: An osteogenesis imperfecta characterized by craniosynostosis, communicating hydrocephalus, ocular proptosis, marked postnatal growth failure, and distinctive facial appearance.

name: lysinuric protein intolerance
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by the body's inability to effectively break down lysine, arginine and ornithine and by renal hyperdiaminoaciduria, especially lysinuria, and by impaired formation of urea with hyperammonemia after protein ingestion. It has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the amino acid transporter gene SLC7A7 on chromosome 14q11.

name: epithelial and subepithelial dystrophy
descr: A corneal dystrophy that primarily affects the corneal epithelium and its basement membrane.

name: epithelial-stromal TGFBI dystrophy
descr: A corneal dystrophy that is characterized by abnormal deposition of proteins in the cornea and is caused by mutations in TGFBI gene of chromosome 5q.

name: stromal dystrophy
descr: A corneal dystrophy that affects the corneal stroma.

name: corneal endothelial dystrophy
descr: A corneal dystrophy that affects the corneal endothelium and/or the descemet membrane.

name: granular corneal dystrophy 2
descr: An corneal granular dystrophy that is characterized by recurrent erosions and stellate or thorn-like opacification located_in the cornea, hyaline and amyloid deposits in the stroma, and progressive vision loss later in life, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation of transforming growth factor beta-induced gene on chromosome 5q31.1, which encodes keratoepithelin. Abnormalities lead to increased hyaline and amyloid protein deposition and disruption of the corneal surface.

name: Reis-Bucklers corneal dystrophy
descr: An epithelial-stromal TGFBI dystrophy that is characterized by recurrent erosions and irregular geographic opacification located_in the cornea, proteinaceous deposits in the anterior stroma and subepithelium, and progressive early vision loss, and has_material_basis in heterozygous mutation of transforming growth factor beta-induced gene located in chromosome 5q31.1, which encodes keratoepithelin. Abnormalities lead to increased protein deposition and disruption especially of Bowman's membrane of the cornea.

name: Thiel-Behnke corneal dystrophy
descr: An epithelial-stromal TGFBI dystrophy that is characterized by recurrent erosions and honeycomb-shaped opacification located_in the cornea, proteinaceous deposits in the anterior stroma and subepithelium, and progressive early vision loss, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of heterozygous mutation of transforming growth factor beta-induced  gene located in chromosome 5q31.1, which encodes keratoepithelin. Abnormalities lead to increased protein deposition and disruption especially of Bowman's membrane of the cornea.

name: Desbuquois dysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia characterized by short stature, joint laxity, scoliosis, and advanced carpal ossification with a delta phalanx.

name: NUT midline carcinoma
descr: A carcinoma that is characterized by a  BRD4-NUT translocation involving the rearrangement of the bromodomain-containing protein 4 (BRD4) and the gene encoding nuclear protein of the testis (NUT)  at 15q14, BRD4-NUT t(15;19)(q14;q13.1) and arises from midline epithelial structures, most commonly the head, neck, and mediastinum.

name: Feingold syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by variable combinations of microcephaly, limb malformations, esophageal and duodenal atresias, and learning disability/mental retardation.

name: gingival fibromatosis
descr: A gingival overgrowth characterized by benign, slowly progressive, nonhemorrhagic, fibrous enlargement of the oral masticatory mucosa.

name: Holt-Oram syndrome
descr: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by congenital anomalies located_in heart and located_in upper limb.

name: Miller-Dieker lissencephaly syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by classical lissencephaly and distinct facial features and has_material_basis_in submicroscopic deletions of 17p13.3, including the LIS1 gene.

name: salt and pepper syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by severe intellectual disability, epilepsy, scoliosis, choreoathetosis, dysmorphic facial features and altered dermal pigmentation.

name: fetal valproate syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by distinctive facial appearance, a cluster of minor and major anomalies and central nervous system dysfunction.

name: Kindler syndrome
descr: A skin disease characterized by congenital blistering, skin atrophy, photosensitivity, skin fragility, and scaling.

name: Kabuki syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by  multiple congenital anomalies and mental retardation. Other characteristics include a peculiar facial gestalt, short stature, skeletal and visceral abnormalities, cardiac anomalies, and immunological defects.

name: familial erythrocytosis 2
descr: A primary polycythemia that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VHL gene (608537) on chromosome 3p25.

name: childhood onset epileptic encephalopathy
descr: An idiopathic generalized epilepsy characterized by onset of multiple seizure types in the first few years of life and associated with poor prognosis. Affected individuals have cognitive regression and intellectual disability.

name: Perlman syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by polyhydramnios with neonatal macrosomia, nephromegaly, distinctive facial appearance, renal dysplasia, nephroblastomatosis, and predisposition to Wilms tumor. It shows similarities to Beckwith-Wiedemann syndrome.

name: Zika fever
descr: A viral infectious disease that has_material_basis in Zika virus, which is transmitted_by Aedes aegypti mosquitoes and targets neural progenitor cells and  neuronal cells in all stages of maturity and has_symptom fever, has_symptom rash, has_symptom headaches and has_symptom joint pain.

name: Shwachman-Diamond syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by exocrine pancreatic insufficiency, bone marrow failure and skeletal abnormalities.

name: left ventricular noncompaction
descr: An intrinsic cardiomyopathy characterized by distinctive (spongy) morphological appearance of the LV myocardium.

name: Goldberg-Shprintzen syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by intellectual disability, specific facial gestalt and Hirschsprung's disease and that has _material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KIAA1279 gene on chromosome 10q21.1.

name: oculoauricular syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by microcornea, microphthalmia, anterior-segment dysgenesis, cataract, coloboma of various parts of the eye, abnormalities of the retinal pigment epithelium, and rod-cone dystrophy and a particular cleft ear lobule.

name: MEDNIK syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by mental retardation, enteropathy, deafness, peripheral neuropathy, ichthyosis, and keratoderma. It is cause by homozygous mutation in the AP1S1 gene on chromosome 7q22.

name: EAST syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterize by seizures, sensorineural deafness, ataxia, mental retardation, and electrolyte imbalance and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the KCNJ10 gene on chromosome 1q23.

name: Mowat-Wilson syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by distinctive facial features, intellectual disability, delayed development, Hirschsprung disease and has_material_basis_in de novo heterozygous mutation in the ZEB2 gene on chromosome 2q22.

name: Perry syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by parkinsonism, hypoventilation, depression, and weight loss and that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the DCTN1 gene on chromosome 2p13.

name: Pitt-Hopkins syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by intellectual disability and developmental delay, breathing problems, recurrent seizures, and distinctive facial features and that has_material_basis_in heterozygous de novo mutations in the TCF4 gene in chromosome 18q21.

name: Schimke immuno-osseous dysplasia
descr: A spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia characterized by short stature with hyperpigmented macules,  unusual facies, proteinuria with progressive renal failure, lymphopenia with recurrent infections, and cerebral ischaemia. It has_material_basis_in mutations in the SMARCAL1 gene.

name: SPOAN syndrome
descr: A neurodegenerative disease characterized by spastic paraplegia, axonal neuropathy, dysarthria, acoustic startle, and congenital optical atrophy and that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KLC2 gene on chromosome 11q13.2.

name: chicken egg allergy
descr: An egg allergy triggered by Gallus gallus eggs.

name: shellfish allergy
descr: A food allergy triggered by Crustacea or Mollusca.

name: respiratory allergy
descr: An allergic hypersensitiity disease located_in the respiratory tract.

name: pollen allergy
descr: A respiratory allergy triggered by pollen.

name: Timothy grass allergy
descr: A pollen allergy triggered by Phleum pratense pollen.

name: autoimmune neuropathy
descr: An autoimmune disease of central nervous system caused by an autoimmune response.

name: drug allergy
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease triggered by a drug.

name: metal allergy
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease triggered by a metal.

name: gastrointestinal allergy
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease located_in the gastrointestinal tract.

name: fruit allergy
descr: A food allergy triggered by a plant fruit product.

name: apple allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Malus domestica plant fruit food product.

name: apricot allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus armeniaca plant fruit food product.

name: cherry allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus avium plant fruit food product.

name: Indian plum allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Ziziphus mauritiana plant fruit food product.

name: orange allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Citrus sinensis plant fruit food product.

name: melon allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Cucumis melo plant fruit food product.

name: peach allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus persica plant fruit food product.

name: plum allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Prunus domestica plant fruit food product.

name: tomato allergy
descr: A fruit allergy triggered by Solanum lycopersicum plant fruit food product.

name: fish allergy
descr: A food allergy triggered by fish.

name: Atlantic cod allergy
descr: A fish allergy triggered by Gadus morhua.

name: Atlantic salmon allergy
descr: A fish allergy triggered by Salmo salar.

name: carp allergy
descr: A fish allergy triggered by Cyprinus carpio.

name: zebrafish allergy
descr: A fish allergy triggered by Danio rerio.

name: rainbow trout allergy
descr: A fish allergy triggered by Oncorhynchus mykiss.

name: beta-lactam allergy
descr: A drug allergy triggered by a beta-lactam.

name: penicillin allergy
descr: A beta-lactam allergy triggered by penicillin.

name: cow milk allergy
descr: A milk allergy triggered by Bos taurus milk.

name: goat milk allergy
descr: A milk allergy triggered by Capra hircus milk.

name: mollusc allergy
descr: A shellfish allergy triggered by Mollusca.

name: crustacean allergy
descr: A shellfish allergy triggered by Crustacea.

name: brown shrimp allergy
descr: A crustacean allergy triggered by Farfantepenaeus aztecus.

name: crab allergy
descr: A crustacean allergy triggered by Scylla paramamosain.

name: Indian prawn allergy
descr: A crustacean allergy triggered by Fenneropenaeus indicus.

name: tiger prawn allergy
descr: A crustacean allergy triggered by Penaeus monodon.

name: white shrimp allergy
descr: A crustacean allergy triggered by Litopenaeus vannamei.

name: snail allergy
descr: A mollusc allergy triggered by snails.

name: latex allergy
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease triggered by latex.

name: hepatoid adenocarcinoma
descr: An adenocarcinoma with morphologic characteristics similar to hepatocellular carcinoma, arising from an anatomic site other than the liver.

name: Warsaw breakage syndrome
