descr: A late onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous triplication of the alpha-synuclein gene on chromosome 4q22.

name: Parkinson's disease 23
descr: An early-onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS13C gene on chromosome 15q22.

name: Parkinson's disease 17
descr: A late-onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the VPS35 gene on chromosome 16q13.

name: Parkinson's disease 20
descr: An early-onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the SYNJ1 gene on chromosome 21q22.

name: Parkinson's disease 14
descr: A late-onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the PLA2G6 gene on chromosome 22q13.

name: Waldenstroem's macroglobulinemia
descr: A lymphoplasmacytic lymphoma characterized by the accumulation of monoclonal cells in the bone marrow and peripheral lymphoid tissues, and associated with the production of serum immunoglobulin M (IgM) monoclonal protein.

name: Norman-Roberts syndrome
descr: A lissencephaly that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the gene encoding reelin (RELN) on chromosome 7q22.

name: thrombosis
descr: A vascular disease caused by the formation of a blood clot inside a blood vessel, obstructing the flow of blood through the circulatory system.

name: karyomegalic interstitial nephritis
descr: An interstitial nephritis characterized by nephritis, interstitial fibrosis, and enlarged and atypical tubular epithelial cell nuclei that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the FAN1 gene on chromosome 15q13.3.

name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria type 8
descr: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the HTRA2 gene on chromosome 2p13.

name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria type 9
descr: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the TIMM50 gene on chromosome 19q13.

name: blastoma
descr: A cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from precursor cells called blast cells.

name: myeloid neoplasm
descr: A bone marrow cancer that is formed of any one of the bone marrow cells belonging to the granulocytic (neutrophil, eosinophil, basophil), monocytic/macrophage, erythroid, megakaryocytic and mast cell lineages.

name: Seckel syndrome 9
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the TRAIP gene on chromosome 3p21.

name: Seckel syndrome 6
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CEP63 gene on chromosome 3q22.

name: Seckel syndrome 1
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the ATR gene on chromosome 3q23.

name: Seckel syndrome 10
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the NSMCE2 gene on chromosome 8q24.

name: Seckel syndrome 8
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the DNA2 gene on chromosome 10q21.

name: Seckel syndrome 4
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CENPJ gene on chromosome 13q12.

name: Seckel syndrome 7
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the NIN gene on chromosome 14q22.

name: Seckel syndrome 5
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the CEP152 gene on chromosome 15q21.

name: Seckel syndrome 2
descr: A Seckel syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the RBBP8 gene on chromosome 18q11.

name: autosomal dominant dyskeratosis congenita 1
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of TERC on chromosome 3q26.2.

name: autosomal recessive dyskeratosis congenita 1
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of NOLA3 on chromosome 15q14.

name: autosomal dominant dyskeratosis congenita 2
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of TERT on chromosome 5p15.33.

name: autosomal recessive dyskeratosis congenita 2
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of NOLA2 on chromosome 5q35.3.

name: autosomal dominant dyskeratosis congenita 3
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of TINF2 on chromosome 14q12.

name: autosomal recessive dyskeratosis congenita 3
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of WRAP53 on chromosome 17p13.1.

name: autosomal dominant dyskeratosis congenita 4
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of RTEL1 on chromosome 20q13.33.

name: autosomal recessive dyskeratosis congenita 4
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of TERT on chromosome 5p15.33.

name: autosomal recessive dyskeratosis congenita 5
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of RTEL1 on chromosome 20q13.33.

name: autosomal dominant dyskeratosis congenita 6
descr: A dyskeratosis congenita that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of ACD on chromosome 16q22.1.

name: autosomal recessive dyskeratosis congenita 6

descr: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutations in the COL2A1 gene which results_in short stature and multiple skeletal abnormalities (lordosis, scoliosis, flattened vertebrae, pectus carinatum, coxa vara, clubfoot, and abnormal epiphyses or metaphyses).

name: spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia, Missouri type
descr: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutations in the MMP13 gene which results_in a pear-shaped vertebrae, abnormal metaphyseal changes, and genu varum deformities.

name: fibrous dysplasia
descr: A bone remodeling disease that results_in the destruction of normal bone and replacing it with fibrous bone tissue.

name: craniodiaphyseal dysplasia
descr: An osteosclerosis that results_in increased calcium concentration located_in skull which decreases the size of cranium foramina and cervical spinal canal.

name: craniometaphyseal dysplasia
descr: An osteosclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutations in the ANKH gene which results_in progressive thickening located_in skull and abnormally shaped ends of long bones in the limbs.

name: SOST-related sclerosing bone dysplasia
descr: A hyperostosis that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the SOST gene which results_in overgrowth of endosteal bone producing dense and wide bones throughout the body especially located_in skull.

name: Worth's syndrome
descr: A hyperostosis that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the LRP5 gene which results_in increased bone density and bony structures located_in palate.

name: pycnodysostosis
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the CTSK gene which results_in dwarfism, brittle bones, osteopetrosis, shortening of the distal phalanges.

name: axial osteomalacia
descr: An osteosclerosis that results_in coarsening located_in trabecular bone.

name: fibrogenesis imperfecta ossium
descr: A syndrome that involves abnormality of collagen synthesis in lamellar bones, with manifestations limited to the skeleton. The initial symptom is frequently spontaneous fractures.

name: hypochondroplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FGFR3 gene which affects ossification of cartilage and results_in short limb dwarfism.

name: achondrogenesis
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in deficient endochondral ossification which results_in dwarfism, short-trunk, short-limbed, anascara, disaprportionately large cranium, and a narrow chest which leads to death in utero or during early neonatal period.

name: hypochondrogenesis
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the COL2A1 gene which affects bone growth and results_in a small body, hydrops fetalis, and abnormal ossification located_in vertebral column or located_in pelvis. The disease has_symptom enlarged abdomen.

name: Kniest dysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the COL2A1 gene which results_in dwarfism with a short trunk and limbs as well as vision and hearing problems. The disease has_symptom large joints, has_symptom wide set eyes, has_symptom round flat face.

name: pseudoachondroplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutations in the COMP gene which results_in short limb dwarfism.

name: acromesomelic dysplasia
descr: An osteochondrodysplasia that has_material_basis_in mesomelia and acromelia, which results_in short limb dwarfism.

name: acromesomelic dysplasia, Maroteaux type
descr: An acromesomelic dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in NPR-B receptor which results_in severe dwarfism, abnormalities of the vertebral column and shortening of the limb middle and distal segments.

name: acromesomelic dysplasia, Hunter-Thompson type
descr: An acromesomelic dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in AMDH gene which results_in normal axial skeleton but fused bones in the located_in hand or located_in foot.

name: acromesomelic dysplasia, Grebe type
descr: An acromesomelic dysplasia that has_material_basis_in mutation in CDMP-1 which results_in micromelia, absence of middle and proximal phalanges and some metacarpal and metatarsal bones.

name: Albright's hereditary osteodystrophy
descr: An pseudohypoparathyroidism that has_material_basis_in lack of responsiveness to parathyroid  hormone which results in shortening and widening of long bones of the located in hand or located in foot along with short stature, obesity, and rounded face.

name: achondrogenesis type IA
descr: An achondrogenesis that results_in abnormal ossification of the located_in vertebral column or located_in spine.

name: achondrogenesis type IB
descr: An achondrogenesis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SLC26A2 gene which results_in umbilical or inguinal hernia and a prominent rounded abdomen.

name: achondrogenesis type II
descr: An achondrogenesis that has_material_basis_in mutations in the COL2A1 gene which results_in underdeveloped lungs, hydrops fetalis, a prominent forehead and abnormal ossification of the located_in vertebral column or located_in pelvis.

name: autosomal recessive spinocerebellar ataxia 2
descr: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by juvenile onset of progressive cerebellar ataxia, axonal sensorimotor peripheral neuropathy, and increased serum alpha-fetoprotein, and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the senataxin gene on chromosome 9q34.

name: Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 5
descr: A Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease that is characterized by pyramidal features including extensor plantar responses, mild increase in tone, and preserved or increased reflexes but no spastic gait.

name: Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 6
descr: A Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease that is characterized by early-onset optic atrophy resulting in progressive visual loss and peripheral axonal sensorimotor neuropathy with highly variable age at onset and severity.

name: Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 7
descr: A Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease that is characterized by optic atrophy followed by retinitis pigmentosa.

name: Neu-Laxova syndrome 2
descr: A serine deficiency that is characterized by multiple fatal malformations including ichthyosis, microcephaly, central nervous system abnormalities, limb deformities, intrauterine growth restriction, proptosis, anasarca, and micrognathia, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the PSAT1 gene on chromosome 9q21.1, causing issues producing the amino acid serine.

name: Neu-Laxova syndrome 1
descr: A serine deficiency that is characterized by multiple fatal malformations including ichthyosis, microcephaly, central nervous system abnormalities, limb deformities, intrauterine growth restriction, proptosis, anasarca, and micrognathia, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the PHGDH gene on chromosome 1p12, causing issues producing the amino acid serine.

name: nonsyndromic congenital nail disorder 4
descr: A nail disease that is characterized by absence of fingernails and toenails, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the R-spondin-4 gene on chromosome 20p13.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 1
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous, homozygous, or compound heterozygous mutation in the desmin gene on chromosome 2q35.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 2
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the alpha-B-crystallin gene on chromosome 11q23.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 3
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the TTID gene on chromosome 5q31.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 4
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the ZASP gene on chromosome 10.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 5
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the FLNC gene on chromosome 7q32.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 6
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the BAG3 gene on chromosome 10q26.

name: myofibrillar myopathy 7
descr: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KY gene on chromosome 3q22.

name: myopathy, lactic acidosis, and sideroblastic anemia
microcephaly and chorioretinopathy 1
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by delayed psychomotor development and visual impairment, often accompanied by short stature and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the TUBGCP6 gene.

name: microcephaly and chorioretinopathy 2
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by delayed psychomotor development, visual impairment, and short stature and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the PLK4 gene.

name: microcephaly and chorioretinopathy 3
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by congenital microcephaly and chorioretinal dysplasia associated with poor vision and nystagmus and has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the TUBGCP4 gene.

name: myoglobinuria
descr: A myopathy that is characterized by an increased urinary excretion of myoglobin.

name: infantile myofibromatosis
descr: A connective tissue benign neoplasm that is characterized by the development of benign tumors in the skin, striated muscles, bones, and in exceptional cases, visceral organs.

name: multiple pterygium syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by permanently bent fingers, short stature, rocker-bottom or club feet, joints that are bent in a fixed position, union or webbing of the skin between the fingers, and/or webbing of the neck, inside bend of the elbows, back of the knees and armpits.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 1
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by onset at birth of lactic acidosis, hypotonia, hypoglycemia, failure to thrive, encephalopathy, and delayed psychomotor development and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the nuclear-encoded BCS1L gene on chromosome 2q35.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 3
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCRB gene on chromosome 8q22.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 4
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCRQ gene on chromosome 5q31.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 5
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by neonatal onset of severe metabolic acidosis associated with hyperammonemia and hypoglycemia and that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCRC2 gene on chromosome 16p12.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 6
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by onset in early childhood of episodic acute lactic acidosis, ketoacidosis, and insulin-responsive hyperglycemia, usually associated with infection and that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CYC1 gene on chromosome 8q24.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 7
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCC2 gene on chromosome 6p21.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 8
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by childhood onset of progressive neurodegeneration that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the LYRM7 gene on chromosome 5q23.

name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 9
descr: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCC3 gene on chromosome 11q12.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 1
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by onset between the second and fifth decades of life of ptosis, progressive external ophthalmoplegia, gastrointestinal dysmotility, cachexia, diffuse leukoencephalopathy, peripheral neuropathy, and mitochondrial dysfunction, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the nuclear-encoded thymidine phosphorylase gene on chromosome 22q13.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 2
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by childhood onset of muscle weakness associated with depletion of mtDNA in skeletal muscle, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the mitochondrial thymidine kinase gene on chromosome 16q21.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 3
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by onset in infancy of progressive liver failure and neurologic abnormalities, hypoglycemia, and increased lactate in body fluids, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the deoxyguanosine kinase gene on chromosome 2p13.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 4a
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by a clinical triad of psychomotor retardation, intractable epilepsy, and liver failure in infants and young children, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the nuclear gene encoding mitochondrial DNA polymerase gamma on chromosome 15q26.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 4b
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by chronic gastrointestinal dysmotility and pseudoobstruction, cachexia, progressive external ophthalmoplegia, axonal sensory ataxic neuropathy, and muscle weakness, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of compound heterozygous mutation in the mitochondrial DNA polymerase gamma gene on chromosome 15q26.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 5
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by infantile onset of hypotonia, progressive neurologic deterioration, a hyperkinetic-dystonic movement disorder, external ophthalmoplegia, deafness, and variable renal tubular dysfunction, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the beta subunit of the succinate-CoA ligase gene on chromosome 13q14.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 6
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by infantile onset of progressive liver failure, often leading to death in the first year of life, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the mitochondrial inner membrane protein MPV17 gene on chromosome 2p23.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 7
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by progressive ataxia, hypotonia, hyporeflexia, athetosis and sensory impairment and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the C10ORF2 gene, which encodes the twinkle and twinky proteins, on chromosome 10q24.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 8a
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by neonatal hypotonia, lactic acidosis, and neurologic deterioration, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the ribonucleotide reductase regulatory TP53 inducible subunit M2B gene on chromosome 8q22.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 9
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by infantile onset of hypotonia, lactic acidosis, severe psychomotor retardation, progressive neurologic deterioration, and excretion of methylmalonic acid, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the alpha subunit of the succinate-CoA ligase gene on chromosome 2p11.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 11
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by onset in childhood or adulthood of progressive external ophthalmoplegia (PEO), muscle weakness and atrophy, exercise intolerance, and respiratory insufficiency due to muscle weakness, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous mutation in the mitochondrial genome maintenance exonuclease 1 gene on chromosome 20p11.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 12a
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by severe hypotonia due to mitochondrial dysfunction apparent at birth and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of heterozygous mutation in the solute carrier family 25 member 4 gene on chromosome 4q35.

name: mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome 13
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by early infantile onset of encephalopathy, hypotonia, lactic acidosis, and severe global developmental delay, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous mutation in the F-box and leucine-rich repeat protein 4 gene on chromosome 6q16.

name: Sengers syndrome
descr: A mitochondrial DNA depletion syndrome that is characterized by congenital cataracts, hypertrophic cardiomyopathy, skeletal myopathy, exercise intolerance, and lactic acidosis, but normal mental development, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the acylglycerol kinase gene on chromosome 7q34.

name: multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome 1
descr: A multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome that is characterized by weakness, respiratory failure, lack of neurologic development, lactic acidosis, and early death, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the NFU1 iron-sulfur cluster scaffold gene on chromosome 2p13.

name: multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome 2
descr: A multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome that is characterized by increased serum glycine and lactate, developmental regression in infancy, an encephalopathic disease course with seizures, spasticity, loss of head control, and abnormal movement, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous mutation in the bolA family member 3 gene on chromosome 2p13.

name: multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome 3
descr: A multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome that is characterized by loss of previously acquired developmental milestones in the first months or years of life, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous mutation in the iron-sulfur cluster assembly factor IBA57 gene on chromosome 1q42.

name: multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome 4
descr: A multiple mitochondrial dysfunctions syndrome that is characterized by normal development for the first months of life, followed by progressive loss of motor and social skills with hypotonia, spasticity, and nystagmus, resulting in death in early childhood, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the iron-sulfur cluster assembly 2 gene on chromosome 14q24.

name: multiple congenital anomalies-hypotonia-seizures syndrome 1
descr: A multiple congenital anomalies-hypotonia-seizures syndrome that is characterized by neonatal hypotonia, lack of psychomotor development, seizures, dysmorphic features, and variable congenital anomalies involving the cardiac, urinary, and gastrointestinal systems and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the PIGN gene on chromosome 18q21.

name: multiple congenital anomalies-hypotonia-seizures syndrome 2
descr: A multiple congenital anomalies-hypotonia-seizures syndrome that is characterized by X-linked recessive inheritance of dysmorphic features, neonatal hypotonia, myoclonic seizures and variable abnormalities involving the central nervous, cardiac, and urinary systems that has_material_basis_in mutation in the PIGA gene on chromosome Xp22.

name: multiple congenital anomalies-hypotonia-seizures syndrome 3
descr: A multiple congenital anomalies-hypotonia-seizures syndrome that is characterized by neonatal hypotonia, lack of psychomotor development, seizures, dysmorphic features, and variable congenital anomalies involving the cardiac, urinary, and gastrointestinal systems and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the PIGT gene on chromosome 20q13.

name: congenital fibrosis of the extraocular muscles
descr: An ocular motility disease that is characterized by the inability to move the eyes in certain directions, droopy eyelids and eyes that are fixed in an abnormal position.

name: childhood acute lymphocytic leukemia
descr: An acute lymphocytic leukemia occuring during childhood.

name: T-cell childhood acute lymphocytic leukemia
descr: A childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia that has_material_basis in T-cells.

name: B-cell childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia
descr: A childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia that has_material_basis in B-cells.

name: lymphoblastic lymphoma
descr: A lymphoma that has_material_basis_in immature malignant lymphocytes (lymphoblasts) committed to the B-cell or T-cell lineage and located_in primarily lymph nodes or located_in extranodal sites.

name: T-cell childhood lymphoblastic lymphoma
descr: A lymphoblastic lymphoma that has_material_basis_in T-cells and that occurs during childhood.

name: adult acute monocytic leukemia
descr: An acute monocytic leukemia occurring in adults.

name: adrenocorticotropic hormone deficiency
descr: A hypopituitarrium that is characterized by a decreased or absent production of adrenocorticotropic hormone by the pituitary gland.

name: medium chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency
descr: A lipid metabolism disorder that is characterized by a deficiency of the enzyme medium chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase that results in the inability to convert medium chain fatty acids to energy, particularly during fasting.

name: short chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency
descr: A lipid metabolism disorder that is characterized by deficiency of the enzyme short chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase that results in the inability to convert short chain fatty acids.

name: very long chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency
descr: A lipid metabolism disorder that is characterized by deficiency of the enzyme very long chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase that results in the inability to convert very long chain fatty acids.

name: X-linked adrenal hypoplasia congenita
descr: An adrenal cortical hypofunction that is characterized by a reduction in adrenal gland function resulting from incomplete development of the adrenal cortex and has_material_basis_in the nuclear receptor NR0B1 (DAX1) gene.

name: herpes simplex virus keratitis
descr: A keratitis that has_material_basis_in herpes simplex type infection.

name: Cryptococcal meningitis
descr: A fungal meningitis that has_material_basis in Crypococcus fungal infection.

name: Cytomegalovirus retinitis
descr: A retinitis that has_material_basis_in Cytomegalovirus.

name: cutaneous candidiasis
descr: A candidiasis that is characterized by Candida infection located_in the skin.

name: lupus nephritis
descr: A glomerulonephritis that is characterized by inflammation of the kidneys resulting from systemic lupus erythematosus.

name: otulipenia
descr: An immune system disease that is characterized by neonatal onset of recurrent fever, erythematous rash with painful nodules, painful joints, and lipodystrophy and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous loss-of-function mutations in the OTULIN gene encoding a deubiquitinase with linear linkage specificity on chromosome 5p15.

name: myeloid and lymphoid neoplasms with eosinophilia and abnormalities of PDGFRA, PDGFRB, and FGFR1
descr: A myeloid neoplasm that is characterized by the formation of abnormal fusion genes that encode constitutively activated tyrosine kinases.

name: myeloid and lymphoid neoplasms associated with PDGFRA rearrangement
descr: A myeloid and lymphoid neoplasms with eosinophilia and abnormalities of PDGFRA, PDGFRB, and FGFR1 that is characterized by the rearrangement of the PDGFRA gene, most often resulting in the formation of FIP1L1-PDGFRA fusion transcripts.

name: myeloid neoplasms associated with PDGFRB rearrangement
descr: A myeloid and lymphoid neoplasms with eosinophilia and abnormalities of PDGFRA, PDGFRB, and FGFR1 that is characterized by the rearrangement of the PDGFRB gene, most often resulting in the formation of ETV6-PDGFRB fusion transcripts.

name: myeloid and lymphoid neoplasms associated with FGFR1 abnormalities
descr: A myeloid and lymphoid neoplasms with eosinophilia and abnormalities of PDGFRA, PDGFRB, and FGFR1 that is characterized by the rearrangement of the FGFR1 gene, resulting in translocations with an 8p11 breakpoint.

name: tricuspid atresia
descr: A tricuspid valve disease characterized by a missing or abnormally developed tricuspid heart value at birth.

name: normophosphatemic familial tumoral calcinosis
descr: A calcinosis that is characterized by massive periarticular, and seldom visceral, deposition of calcified tumors.

name: esophageal atresia/tracheoesophageal fistula
descr: A gastrointestinal system disease that is characterized by abnormal development of the esophagus and trachea where the upper esophagus does not connect (atresia) to the lower esophagus and stomach and may also include tracheoesophageal fistula where the esophagus and the trachea are abnormally connected which allows fluids from the esophagus to get into the airways and interfere with breathing.

name: thiopurine S-methyltransferase deficiency
descr: An inherited metabolic disease that is characterized by significantly reduced activity of an enzyme that helps the body process drugs called thiopurines.

name: bladder exstrophy-epispadias-cloacal exstrophy complex
descr: A physical disorder that is characterized as a spectrum of anomalies involving the urinary tract, genital tract, musculoskeletal system and sometimes the intestinal tract.

name: bladder exstrophy
descr: A bladder exstrophy-epispadias-cloacal exstrophy complex that is characterized by an evaginated bladder plate, epispadias and an anterior defect of the pelvis, pelvic floor and abdominal wall. The rear portion of the bladder wall (posterior vesical wall) turns outward (exstrophy) through an opening in the abdominal wall and urine is excreted through this opening.

name: cloacal exstrophy
descr: A bladder exstrophy-epispadias-cloacal exstrophy complex that is characterized by a defect in the urethra, bladder and bowel.

name: meningococcal meningitis
descr: A bacterial meningitis that has_material_basis_in Neisseria meningitidis infection.

name: hepatic veno-occlusive disease
descr: A hepatic vascular disease that is characterized by obstruction of some of the small veins of the liver.

name: mucositis
descr: A gastrointestinal system disease that is characterized by painful inflammation and ulceration of the mucous membranes lining the digestive tract.

name: haemophilus meningitis
descr: A bacterial meningitis that has_material_basis_in Haemophilus influenzae infection.

name: Zika virus congenital syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized in neonates by microcephaly, craniofacial disproportion, spasticity, seizures, irritability and brainstem dysfunction including feeding difficulties, ocular abnormalities and findings on neuroimaging such as calcifications, cortical disorders and ventriculomegaly and has_material_basis_in the acquisition of Zika virus infection in utero.

name: PHARC syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease that is characterized by polyneuropathy, hearing loss, cerebellar ataxia, retinitis pigmentosa and early-onset cataract.

name: mixed fibrolamellar hepatocellular carcinoma
descr: A fibrolamellar carcinoma that is characteirzed by the presence of both pure fibrolamellar hepatocellular carcinoma and and conventional hepatocellular carcinoma components.

name: medullary colon carcinoma
descr: A colon carcinoma that is characterized by a solid growth pattern.

name: mixed mucinous and nonmucinous bronchioloalveolar adenocarcinoma
descr: A bronchiolo-alveolar adenocarcinoma that is characterized by a mixed array of different patterns (acinar, papillary, bronchioloalveolar, solid with mucin).

name: mucinous bronchioloalveolar adenocarcinoma
descr: A bronchiolo-alveolar adenocarcinoma that is characterized by a tumour cells containing abundant mucin in their cytoplasm and composed of tall columnar cells growing along alveolar walls without stromal invasion.

name: nonmucinous bronchioloalveolar adenocarcinoma
descr: A bronchiolo-alveolar adenocarcinoma that is characterized by cells with cuboidal or columnar morphology with eosinophilic or clear cytoplasm and shows Clara cell or type 2 pneumocyte differentiation.

name: chronic neutrophilic leukemia
descr: A chronic leukemia characterized by neutrophilic leukocytosis with no detectable Philadelphia chromosome or BCR/ABL fusion gene.

name: chronic myelomonocytic leukemia
descr: A chronic leukemia characterized by monocytosis, increased monocytes in the bone marrow, variable degrees of dysplasia, but an absence of immature granulocytes in the blood.

name: malignant hemangioma
descr: A cell type cancer of vascular origin that is characterized by the proliferation of endothelial cells in and about the vascular lumen.

name: malignant epithelioid hemangioendothelioma
descr: A malignant hemangioma characterized by the presence of epithelioid endothelial cells. The neoplastic cells are arranged in cords and nests, which are embedded in a myxoid to hyalinized stroma.

name: PTEN hamartoma tumor syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized as a spectrum of disorders (Cowden syndrome, Bannayan-Riley-Ruvalcaba syndrome, PTEN-related Proteus syndrome, and Proteus-like syndrome) caused by germline mutations of the PTEN gene.

name: relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma
descr: A diffuse large B-cell lymphoma characterized by less than 50 percent decrease in lesion size with induction therapy or the appearance of new lesions or the appearance of new lesions after attainment of complete remission.

name: superior semicircular canal dehiscence
descr: An inner ear disease characterized by dehiscence in the bone overlying the superior semicircular canal experience with symptoms of pressure or sound-induced vertigo, bone conduction hyperacusis, and pulsatile tinnitus.

name: Carey-Fineman-Ziter syndrome
descr: A syndrome characterized by hypotonia, Moebius sequence (bilateral congenital facial palsy with impairment of ocular abduction), Pierre Robin complex (micrognathia, glossoptosis, and high-arched or cleft palate), delayed motor milestones, and failure to thrive.

name: Marinesco-Sjogren syndrome
descr: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by congenital cataracts, cerebellar ataxia, progressive muscle weakness due to myopathy, and delayed psychomotor development.

name: mandibulofacial dysostosis, Guion-Almeida type
descr: An autosomal dominant disease characterized by progressive microcephaly, micrognathia, microtia, dysplastic ears, preauricular skin tags, speech delay, significant developmental delay,  midface and malar hypoplasia.

name: congenital muscular dystrophy with cataracts and intellectual disability
descr: A congenital muscular dystrophy characterized by onset of progressive muscle weakness in early childhood with autosomal recessive inheritance that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the INPP5K gene (607875) on chromosome 17p13.

name: infantile histiocytoid cardiomyopathy
descr: An intrinsic cardiomyopathy characterized by the presence of characteristic pale granular foamy histiocyte-like cells within the myocardium and has_material_basis_in a mutation in the gene encoding mitochondrial cytochrome b.

name: colorectal carcinoma
descr: A colorectal cancer that arises from the colon or rectum and invades through the muscularis mucosa into the submucosa.

name: bilateral renal aplasia
descr: A renal agenesis that is characterized by the absence of both kidneys at birth.

name: Peters plus syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by anterior chamber eye anomalies, short limbs with broad distal extremities, characteristic facial features, cleft lip/palate, and variable developmental delay/intellectual disability.

name: adenoid cystic carcinoma
descr: An adenocarcinoma that is characterized by bands or cylinders of hyalinized or mucinous stroma separating or surrounded by nests or cords of small epithelial cells.

name: renal hypoplasia
descr: A kidney disease that is characterized by abnormally small kidneys with normal morphology and reduced number of nephrons.

name: CAKUT
descr: A urinary system disease characterized by structural malformations in the kidney and/or urinary tract containing vesicoureteral reflux.

name: CAKUT1
descr: A CAKUT that has_material_ basis_in heterozygous mutation in the DSTYK gene on chromosome 1q32.

name: CAKUT2
descr: A CAKUT that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the TBX18 gene on chromosome 6q14.

name: non-alcoholic fatty liver disease
descr: A fatty liver disease characterized by the storing of excess fat in liver cells which is not caused by heavy alcohol use.

name: sideroblastic anemia with B-cell immunodeficiency, periodic fevers, and developmental delay
descr: A sideroblastic anemia characterized by onset of severe sideroblastic anemia in the neonatal period or infancy, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the TRNT1 gene on chromosome 3p26.

name: primary mediastinal B-cell lymphoma
descr: A diffuse large B-cell lymphoma that is is characterized by a diffuse proliferation of medium to large B-cells associated with sclerosis.

name: nodal marginal zone lymphoma
descr: A marginal zone B-cell lymphoma  which morphologically resembles lymph nodes involved by marginal zone lymphomas of extranodal or splenic types, but without evidence of extranodal or splenic disease.

name: polycystic kidney disease 4
descr: A autosomal recessive polycystic kidney disease that has_material_basis_in mutation in the PKD4 gene.

name: early infantile epileptic encephalopathy 8
descr: An early infantile epileptic encephalopathy characterized by seizures with onset before 2 years of age, severe developmental delay, and in some patients hyperekplexia that has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive inheritance of a mutation in the ARHGEF9 gene on chromosome Xq22.1.

name: lysosomal and lipase deficiency
descr: A lipid storage disease characterized by lysosomal and lipase deficiency.

name: pseudohypoparathyroidism type IB
descr: A pseudohypoparathyroidism characterized by isolated renal parathyroid hormone (PTH) resistance resulting in hypocalcemia, hyperphosphatemia and elevated PTH levels that has_material_basis_in mutations that alter the methylation pattern of GNAS on 20q13.32.

name: epidermolytic palmoplantar keratoderma
descr: A palmoplantar keratosis that is characterized by marked hyperkeratosis on the surface of palms and soles.

name: autosomal dominant dystrophic epidermolysis bullosa
