descr: An intestinal disease located_in the cecum.

name: cecum carcinoma
descr: A cecum cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

name: colon carcinoma
descr: A colon cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

name: cecum cancer
descr: A large intestine cancer that is located_in the cecum.

name: pleural disease
descr: A thoracic disease which may involve inflammation of pleura, collection of air within the pleural cavity, abnormal collection of pleural fluid, abnormal growths on the pleura (pleural tumor) and pleural plaques. The main causes of pleural diseases including pleural effusions are congestive heart failure, malignancy, parapneumonic infections and pulmonary embolism.

name: mixed cell type cancer
descr: A cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from two germinal layers of tissue.

name: parathyroid carcinoma
descr: An endocrine gland cancer located_in the parathyroid glands located in the neck.

name: head and neck carcinoma
descr: A head and neck cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells and is located in the upper aerodigestive tract, including the lip, oral cavity (mouth), nasal cavity, paranasal sinuses, pharynx, and larynx.

name: urticaria
descr: A skin disease characterized by skin rash notable for pale red, raised and itchy bumps, located_in the upper dermis.

name: arthus reaction
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type III disease that is characterized by local vasculitis, has_symptom pain, edema, hemorrhage, or necrosis, and has_material_basis_in deposition of antigen-antibody immune complexes in vascular or serosal walls.

name: hypersensitivity reaction type III disease
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction disease that is characterized by the accumulation of antigen-antibody immune complexes, causing an inflammatory response and injury.

name: angioedema
descr: A skin disease characterized by the rapid swelling of the dermis, subcutaneous tissue, mucosa and submucosal tissues.

name: cognitive disorder
descr: A disease of mental health that affects cognitive functions including memory processing, perception and problem solving.

name: chromoblastomycosis
descr: A subcutaneous mycosis that is a chronic subcutaneous fungal infection, which presents as nodular or verrucoid, ulcerated, or crusted skin lesions on exposed areas of skin caused by Fonsecaea pedrosoi, Fonsecaea compacta, Cladophialophora carrionii or Phialophora verrucosa. Histological examination reveals muriform cells (with perpendicular septations) or thick walled, dark-colored, rounded forms (copper pennies) that are characteristic of this infection.

name: dermatomycosis
descr: A cutaneous mycosis that results in fungal infection located in skin or of its appendages, has_material_basis_in Ascomycota fungi other than the dermatophytes.

name: fungal infectious disease
descr: A disease by infectious agent that results_in infection, has_material_basis_in Fungi, which pass the resistance barriers of the human or animal body.

name: alcohol use disorder
descr: A substance abuse that involves the recurring use of alcoholic beverages despite negative consequences.

name: rheumatic disease
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that involves inflammation or pain in the muscles, joints, or fibrous tissue.

name: respiratory system disease
descr: A disease of anatomical entity that located_in the respiratory system which extends from the nasal sinuses to the diaphragm.

name: laryngeal tuberculosis
descr: A pulmonary tuberculosis causing granulomatous leisons in the larynx resulting from an inflammation caused by mycobacteria leading to hoarseness, dysphagia and odynophagia.

name: acute chest syndrome
descr: A lung disease that involves a vasoocclusive crisis of the pulmonary vasculature seen in patients with sickle cell anemia. The crisis is initiated by a lung infection, and the resulting inflammation and loss of oxygen tension leads to sickling of red cells and further vasoocclusion. The disease has_symptom fever, has_symptom pleuritic chest pain, has_symptom tachypnea, has_symptom cough, has_symptom hypoxemia, has_symptom marked leukocytosis, and has_symptom diffuse infiltrates on chest radiograph.

name: rheumatic fever
descr: A connective tissue disease that develops from an antecedent Group A Streptococcal pharyngeal infection and has_symptom carditis, has_symptom polyarthritis, has_symptom chorea, has_symptom erythema marginatum, has_symptom subcutaneous nodules, has_symptom arthralgia, has_symptom prolonged PR interval, and/or has_symptom fever.

name: thrombocytopenia
descr: A blood platelet disease characterized by low a platelet count in the blood.

name: endogenous depression
descr: A mental depression that is characterized by a dysregulation of the endogenous opioid system and not of the monaminergic system.

name: integumentary system disease
descr: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the integumentary system comprising the skin and its appendages.

name: hypoglycemic coma
descr: A brain disease that is characterized by coma or unconsciousness, develops from a prolonged insufficient supply of glucose to the brain, has_symptom decreased cognition, has_symptom aberrant behavior, has_symptom seizure, and has_symptom coma.

name: keratosis
descr: A skin disease characterized_by growth of keratin on the skin or mucous membranes.

name: breast cancer
descr: A thoracic cancer that originates in the mammary gland.

name: male breast cancer
descr: A breast cancer that occurs in males.

name: breast fibroadenoma
descr: A breast benign neoplasm comprised of fibrous and glandoular tissues located_in breast.

name: cancer
descr: A disease of cellular proliferation that is malignant and primary, characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation, local cell invasion and metastasis.

name: breast leiomyoma
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that has_material_basis in smooth muscle cells.

name: breast adenoma
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that is has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue in which tumor cells form glands or glandlike structures.

name: breast duct papilloma
descr: An intraductal papillary breast neoplasm that is has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue on papillae of vascularized connective tissue.

name: intraductal papillary breast neoplasm
descr: An intraductal breast neoplasm that is characterized by fingerlike growth projections.

name: breast myofibroblastoma
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that derives_from precursor mesenchymal cells with myofibroblastic differentiation.

name: benign breast phyllodes tumor
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that has_material_basis in epithelial and stromal tissue and derives_from periductal stromal cells of the breast.

name: breast papillomatosis
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that is characterized by papillary proliferations within multiple terminal duct-lobular units or in the distal branches (terminal ducts) of the duct system.

name: breast angiomatosis
descr: A breast disease that is characterized by diffuse vascularity surrounding ducts and lobules without invasion, large irregular vascular spaces and flat epithelium without atypia.

name: central nervous system tuberculosis
descr: An extrapulmonary tuberculosis that results in formation of tuberculomas located_in brain or located_in spinal cord.

name: skeletal tuberculosis
descr: An extrapulmonary tuberculosis that results in formation of lesions located in bone.

name: benign breast adenomyoepithelioma
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that is characterized by dual differentiation into luminal cells and myoepithelial cells.

name: breast adenomyoepithelioma
descr: A breast myoepithelial neoplasm that affects the breast and is characterized by biphasic proliferation of both epithelial and myoepithelial cells.

name: female breast upper-inner quadrant cancer
descr: A female breast cancer that is located_in the upper-inner quadrant of the breast.

name: female breast lower-inner quadrant cancer
descr: A female breast cancer that is located_in the lower-inner quadrant of the breast.

name: female breast axillary tail cancer
descr: A female breast cancer that is located_in the breast tissue extending into the axilla.

name: ventricular septal defect
descr: A heart septal defect characterized by an opening in the interventricular septum, causing a shunt between ventricles.

name: supratentorial cancer
descr: A brain cancer that is located in the supratentorial region.

name: malignant pineal area germ cell neoplasm
pineoblastoma
descr: A pineal gland neoplasm located_in the brain.

name: chronic interstitial cystitis
descr: A chronic cystitis characterized by unpleasant sensation related to the bladder and lower urinary tract in the absence of identifiable causes and has_symptom pain, has_symptom pressure, has_symptom discomfort, has_symptom dysuria, and/or has_symptom urinary frequency.

name: cystitis
descr: A bladder disease that is characterized by inflammation of the bladder.

name: glaucoma
descr: An eye disease that is characterized by an unstable or a sustained increase in the intraocular pressure which the eye cannot withstand without damage to its structure or impairment of its function.

name: neuroendocrine tumor
descr: An endocrine gland cancer that has_material_basis_in neuroendocrine cells.

name: ichthyosis
descr: A skin disease characterized by drying and scaling of skin with the accumulation of thick scales and cracks that may be painful or bleed.

name: musculoskeletal system disease
descr: A disease of anatomical entity that occurs in the muscular and/or skeletal system.

name: endocrine gland cancer

name: arteriosclerosis

name: colonic benign neoplasm

name: hemochromatosis

name: myelophthisic anemia

name: anemia

name: post-thrombotic syndrome

name: West Nile encephalitis
descr: A viral infectious disease that results in inflammation located in brain, has_material_basis_in West Nile virus, which is transmitted by Culex, transmitted by Aedes, and transmitted by Anopheles species of mosquitoes. The infection has symptom high fever, has symptom headache, has symptom neck stiffness, has symptom stupor, has symptom disorientation, has symptom coma, has symptom tremors, has symptom convulsions, has symptom muscle weakness, has symptom vision loss, has symptom numbness, and has symptom paralysis.

name: West Nile fever
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection, has_material_basis_in West Nile virus, which is transmitted_by Culex and transmitted_by Aedes mosquitoes. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom sore throat, has_symptom headache, has_symptom body ache, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom maculopapular rash and has_symptom vomiting.

name: gangliosidosis

name: hereditary elliptocytosis
descr: A hematopoietic system disease characterized by oval or elliptical red blood cells, slight or absent hemolysis with little or no anemia; splenomegaly is often present.

name: multiple sclerosis

name: relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis

Symptoms may vary from mild to severe, and relapses and remissions may last for days or months. More than 80 percent of people who have MS begin with relapsing-remitting cycles.

name: neonatal jaundice

name: Wernicke encephalopathy

name: ovarian cancer

name: rhinosporidiosis

Disease of the skin, mouth, upper airways, ear, genitals, and rectum has also been observed.

name: gangliocytoma

name: glomus tumor

name: blepharoconjunctivitis

name: psychotic disorder

name: opportunistic mycosis

name: hereditary spastic paraplegia

name: central nervous system origin vertigo

name: dermatitis

name: idiopathic interstitial pneumonia

Later,it develops loose organizing fibrosis, mostly within alveolar septa and type II pneumocyte hyperplasia. Fever, cough, and difficulty breathing develop over 1 to 2 weeks, typically progressing to acute respiratory failure.

name: nonspecific interstitial pneumonia

Lung biopsies may show predominantly interstitial inflammation or fibrosis or a combination of inflammation and fibrosis. A dry cough and shortness of breath develop over 6 to 18 months. Low-grade fever and a feeling of illness (malaise) may occur.

name: middle lobe syndrome

descr: A parasitic infectious disease that occurs when part of the body is infested with parasitic worms such as cestodes, nematodes and trematodes.

name: metagonimiasis
descr: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine by Metagonimus yokogawai. The symptoms are diarrhea and colicky abdominal pain. The heart and brain can also be infected.

name: sublingual gland cancer
descr: A  salivary gland cancer that is located_in the sublingual gland.

name: fascioliasis
descr: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the bile ducts of the liver by Fasciola hepatica or Fasciola gigantica. During the acute phase, manifestations include abdominal pain, hepatomegaly, fever, vomiting, diarrhea, urticaria and eosinophilia. Occasionally, infection occurs in intestinal wall, lungs, subcutaneous tissue, and pharyngeal mucosa.

name: salivary gland cancer
descr: An oral cavity cancer that is located_in the salivary gland.

name: lupus erythematosus
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is characterized by a constellation of findings that include elevated antibodies to nuclear antigens, antiphospholipids, low complement levels, ulcers, non-scarring alopecia, renal or neurologic damage, and low white blood cell and platelet counts, has_symptom rashes, fatigue, arthritis, hair loss, seizures, and symptoms related to affected organs, and has_material_basis_in autoimmune disorder.

name: acute monocytic leukemia
descr: A monocytic leukemia where the majority of monocytic cells are promonocytes.

name: molluscum contagiosum
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection located_in skin, has_material_basis_in Molluscum contagiosum virus, which is transmitted_by contact with the skin, and transmitted_by fomites. The infection has_symptom lesions which are flesh-colored with a pit in the center.

name: neuromyelitis optica
descr: A central nervous system disease characterized by inflammation of the optic nerve (optic neuritis) and inflammation of the spinal cord (myelitis).

name: penis carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the penis.

name: fasciolopsiasis
descr: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine by Fasciolopsis buski. The symptoms include diarrhea, abdominal pain, fever, ascites, anasarca and intestinal obstruction.

name: psoriasis
descr: A skin disease that is characterized by patches of thick red skin and silvery scales.

name: progressive myoclonus epilepsy
descr: A variable age at onset electroclinical syndrome characterised by a relentlessly progressive disease course until death.

name: tinea nigra
descr: A superficial mycosis that is a superficial fungal infection of the skin characterized by brown to black macules which usually occur on the palmar aspects of hands and occasionally the plantar and other surfaces of the skin, caused by Hortaea werneckii, which is a common saprophytic fungus believed to occur in soil, compost, humus and on wood in humid tropical and sub-tropical regions.

name: dermatophytosis
descr: A cutaneous mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in scalp, located_in glabrous skin, or located_in nail, has_material_basis_in Ascomycota fungi that belong to a group called dermatophytes, which have the ability to utilize keratin as a nutrient source.

name: leukoplakia of vagina
descr: A vaginal disease that is a precancerous lesion that is characterized by the presence of white plaques which cannot be rubbed off. Histology shows increased keratin.

name: skin melanoma
descr: A skin cancer that has_material_basis_in melanocytes.

name: autoimmune thrombocytopenic purpura
descr: A primary thrombocytopenia that involves relatively few platelets in blood as a result of autoantibodies.

name: learning disability
descr: A specific developmental disorder that involves difficulty in scholastic skills such as reading, writing, spelling, reasoning, recalling and/or organizing information resulting from the brain's inability to receive and process information.

name: plantar fascial fibromatosis
descr: A connective tissue disease characterized by progressive fibrosis and thickening located_in the palmar fascia and has_symptom early painless nodules, has_symptom decreased range of motion, has_symptom weakened grip, and has_symptom eventual contracture.

name: seborrheic infantile dermatitis
descr: A seborrheic dermatitis that involves fungal infection of the scalp of recently born babies caused by Malassezia furfur. It is occasionally linked to immune disorders. The symptoms include thick, crusty, yellow or brown scales over the child's scalp.

name: lattice corneal dystrophy
descr: An epithelial-stromal TGFBI dystrophy that is characterized by recurrent erosions and lattice line refractile and fleck-like opacification located_in the cornea, amyloid deposits beginning in the anterior stroma, and progressive vision loss later in life, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation of transforming growth factor beta-induced gene located in chromosome 5q31.1, which encodes keratoepithelin. Abnormalities lead to increased amyloid protein deposition and disruption of the corneal surface.

name: sideroblastic anemia
descr: An aplastic anemia where the bone marrow produces ringed sideroblasts rather than healthy red blood cells (erythrocytes).

name: cowpox
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection in rodents, cows, and humans, located_in skin, has_material_basis_in Cowpox virus, which is transmitted_by contact with an infected animal. The infection results_in_formation_of vesicopustular lesions on the hands or face.

name: metal metabolism disorder
descr: An inherited metabolic disorder that involves metabolic disturbances in the processing or distribution of dietary minerals.

name: subacute sclerosing panencephalitis
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection located_in brain and that  has_material_basis_in Measles virus which is immune resistant.

name: autosomal dominant polycystic kidney disease
descr: A polycystic kidney disease characterized by the presence of multiple cysts located_in the kidney resulting from ciliopathy that disrupts the function of primary cilium, inherited in an autosomal dominant fashion.

name: narcolepsy
descr: A sleep disorder that involves an excessive urge to sleep at inappropriate times, such as while at work.

name: cervix uteri carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the uterine cervix.

name: polycythemia vera
descr: A primary polycythemia and a myeloproliferative neoplasm characterized by erythroid hyperplasia,  myeloid leukocytosis, thrombocytosis, and splenomegaly.

name: degenerative disc disease
descr: A bone deterioration disease that has_material_basis_in gradual dehydration and tears located_in intervertebral disc.

name: sudden infant death syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is characterized by the sudden death of an infant that is not predicted by medical history and remains unexplained after a thorough forensic autopsy and detailed death scene investigation.

name: psoriatic arthritis
descr: A syndrome that occurs in humans with psoriasis who also experience symptoms similar to arthritis.

name: larynx carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the larynx.

name: intestine carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the intestine.

name: parotid gland cancer
descr: A salivary gland cancer that is located_in the parotid gland.

name: uterine cervix leukoplakia
descr: A cervix disease that is characterized by the presence of a hyperkeratotic lesion.

name: Zellweger syndrome
descr: A peroxisomal biogenesis disorder that is characterized by the reduction or absence of functional peroxisomes in the cells of an individual that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of a mutation in the peroxisome biogenesis factor (PEX) genes.

name: bladder carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the bladder.

name: peroxisomal disease
descr: An inherited metabolic disorder that involves peroxisome malfunction.

name: pityriasis versicolor
descr: A superficial mycosis that is a chronic, superficial fungal infection of the skin caused by Malassezia furfur, which is characterized by well-demarcated white, pink, fawn, or brownish lesions, often coalescing, and covered with thin furfuraceous scales.

name: Ritter's disease
descr: A commensal bacterial infectious disease that is characterized by widespread erythema, peeling, and necrosis of the skin, that is caused by a toxin produced by a bacterium of the genus Staphylococcus (S. aureus). The infection has_symptoms redness of skin, has_symptom fluid-filled blister formation, has_symptom fever and has_symptom irritability.

name: leishmaniasis
descr: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by protozoan parasite of the genus Leishmania, which is transmitted by the bite of sand fly (subfamily Phlebotominae).

name: systemic lupus erythematosus
descr: A lupus erythematosus that is an inflammation of connective tissue marked by skin rashes, joint pain and swelling, inflammation of the kidneys and inflammation of the tissue surrounding the heart.

name: anal carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the anus.

name: REM sleep behavior disorder
descr: A sleep disorder that involves abnormal behavior including the acting out of violent or dramatic dreams during the sleep phase with rapid eye movement.

name: esophagus carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the esophagus.

name: sebaceous gland disease
descr: A skin disease that is located_in the sebaceous gland.

name: uterus carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the uterus.

name: cutaneous leishmaniasis
descr: A leishmaniasis that involves skin infection caused by Leishmania species, resulting in one or more cutaneous lesions.

name: granuloma inguinale
descr: A primary bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection located_in skin or located_in mucosa of genital tract, has_material_basis_in Klebsiella granulomatis, transmitted by sexual contact or transmitted_by contact with the open sores. The infection has_symptom painless genital ulcers.

name: acute myeloid leukemia
descr: A myeloid leukemia that is characterized by the rapid growth of abnormal white blood cells that accumulate in the bone marrow and interfere with the production of normal blood cells.

name: amyloidosis
descr: An acquired metabolic disease that has_material_basis_in extracellular tissue deposition of mis-folded proteins called fibrils composed of low molecular weight subunits of a variety of proteins. These deposits may result in a wide range of clinical manifestations depending upon their type, location, and the amount of deposition.

name: eczema herpeticum
descr: A herpes simplex that results_in infection located_in skin, effected by preexisting dermatosis, has_material_basis_in Human herpesvirus 1 or Human herpesvirus 2. The infection has_symptom watery blisters, has_symptom fever, and has_symptom swelling of the lymph nodes.

name: atrophic muscular disease
descr: A neuromuscular disease that is characterized by an abnormal reduction in the muscle volume and atrophy.

name: liver carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the liver.

name: stomach carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the stomach.

name: visceral leishmaniasis
descr: A leishmaniasis that is the most severe form of the disease caused by protozoan parasites of the Leishmania genus, resulting in the infection of the internal organs such as liver, spleen and bone marrow. The symptoms include fever, weight loss, and an enlarged spleen and liver.

name: variola minor
descr: A smallpox that results_in milder infection, located_in skin, has_material_basis_in Variola virus. The infection results_in_formation_of lesions.

name: mucocutaneous leishmaniasis
descr: A leishmaniasis that involves a chronic inflammatory process involving the nasal, pharyngeal, and laryngeal mucosa, which can lead to extensive tissue destruction, caused by protozoan parasites belonging to the genus Leishmania. The infection is characterized by granulomatous lesion which can destroy upper respiratory tract mucosa.

name: gas gangrene
descr: A commensal bacterial infectious disease that results in infection, located in muscle tissue, has_material_basis_in Clostridium perfringens, which produce gas that becomes trapped in the infected tissue. Gas gangrene usually develops after injuries or surgery. The infection has symptom large blisters, has symptom pain in the infected area, has symptom myonecrosis, has symptom gas production, and has symptom sepsis.

name: achalasia
descr: An esophageal disease that is characterized by an inability of the esophagus to move food toward the stomach resulting from the lower esophogeal sphincter not fully relaxing during swallowing.

name: Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome
descr: A X-linked recessive disease that is characterized by abnormal immune system function and a reduced ability to form blood clots resulting from a decrease in the number and size of blood cell fragments involved in clotting (microthrombocytopenia).

name: rectum carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the rectum.

name: amebiasis
descr: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by the amoeba Entamoeba histolytica. Amebic invasion of the intestinal lining causes dysentery, colitis or diarrhea. The infection can also spread through the blood to the liver and, rarely, to the lungs, brain or other organs.

name: speech disorder
descr: A communication disorder that involves difficulty with the act of speech production.

name: lichen planus
descr: A lichen disease that is located_in skin, located_in tongue or located_in oral mucosa, which presents itself in the form of papules, lesions or rashes.

name: periodic limb movement disorder
descr: A sleep disorder that involves involuntary limb movement during sleep.

name: herpes zoster oticus
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in inflammation located_in facial nerve, which leads to paralysis of one side of the face, has_material_basis_in Human herpesvirus 3, which reactivates after appearing as chickenpox in childhood. The infection has_symptom vesicular rash of the ear or mouth, has_symptom tinnitus, has_symptom vertigo, has_symptom otalgia, and has_symptom headache.

name: central sleep apnea
descr: A sleep apnea that is characterized by a malfunction of the basic neurological controls for breathing rate and the failure to give the signal to inhale, causing the individual to miss one or more cycles of breathing.

name: pompholyx
descr: A sweat gland disease that is characterized by recurrent vesicles and bullae that develop particularly upon the lateral palms, soles, and fingers and has_symptom pruritis and cracked skin.

name: kidney carcinoma in situ
descr: An in situ carcinoma that is located_in the kidney.

name: erythromelalgia
descr: A neuropathy that is characterized by intense, burning pain of affected extremities, severe redness and increased skin temperature.

name: Alagille syndrome
descr: A liver disease that is characterized by an accumulation of bile in the liver resulting from a reducted number of liver small bile ducts.

name: cerebral amyloid angiopathy
descr: An amyloidosis where amyloid protein progressively deposits in cerebral blood vessel walls with subsequent degenerative vascular changes that usually result in spontaneous cerebral hemorrhage, ischemic lesions and progressive dementia.

name: Beemer-Langer syndrome
descr: A syndrome that results_in multiple congenital anomalies, including hydrops fetalis, facial and visceral abnormalities, short ribs, and short limbs without polydactyly.

name: acrocallosal syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is an autosomal recessive disorder, which is characterized by corpus callosum agenesis, polydactyly, multiple dysmorphic features, motor and mental retardation.

name: amino acid metabolic disorder
descr: An inherited metabolic disorder that is characterized by impaired synthesis and degradation of amino acids.

name: mast-cell leukemia
descr: A leukemia that results_in an overwhelming number of tissue mast cells located_in peripheral blood.

name: frontotemporal dementia
descr: A dementia characterized by progressive neuronal loss predominantly involving the frontal and/or temporal lobes of the brain resulting in a gradual and progressive decline in behavior or language.

name: colorectal cancer
descr: A large intestine cancer that is located_in the colon and/or located_in the rectum.

name: Waardenburg's syndrome
descr: An autosomal disease characterized by varying degrees of deafness, minor defects in structures arising from the neural crest and pigmentation anomalies of the hair, the skin and/or the iris of both eyes.

name: nasopharynx carcinoma
descr: A pharynx cancer that is located in the nasopharynx, the uppermost region of the pharynx or throat, where the nasal passages and auditory tubes join the remainder of the upper respiratory tract.

name: homocystinuria
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves an accumulation of homocysteine in the serum and an increased excretion of homocysteine in the urine.

name: histidine metabolism disease
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves deficiency in histidine.

name: cystinuria
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves the formation of cystine stones in the kidneys, ureter, and bladder.

name: urea cycle disorder
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves a deficiency of one of the enzymes in the urea cycle which is responsible for removing ammonia from the blood stream.

name: glycine encephalopathy
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves abnormally high levels of the amino acid glycine in bodily fluids and tissues.

name: maple syrup urine disease
descr: An organic acidemia that is caused by a deficiency of decarboxylase leading to high concentrations of valine, leucine, isoleucine, and alloisoleucine in the blood, urine, and cerebrospinal fluid and characterized by an odor of maple syrup to the urine, vomiting, hypertonicity, severe mental retardation, seizures, and eventually death unless the condition is treated with dietary measures.

name: alkaptonuria
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves phenylalanine and tyrosine metabolism with the accumulation of homogentisic acid, a toxic tyrosine byproduct.

name: ornithine carbamoyltransferase deficiency
descr: An urea cycle disorder that involves a mutated and ineffective form of the enzyme ornithine transcarbamylase.

name: citrullinemia
descr: An urea cycle disorder that involves the accumulation of ammonia in the blood.

name: hyperlysinemia
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves an abnormal increase of lysine in the blood.

name: tyrosinemia
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves impaired break down of the amino acid tyrosine.

name: hyperargininemia
descr: An urea cycle disorder that involves arginase deficiency resulting in elevated levels of plasma arginine.

name: hyperhomocysteinemia
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves an abnormally large level of homocysteine in the blood.

name: carbamoyl phosphate synthetase I deficiency disease
descr: A urea cycle disorder that involves accumulation of ammonia in the blood.

name: phenylketonuria
descr: An amino acid metabolic disorder that is characterized by a mutation in the gene for the hepatic enzyme phenylalanine hydroxylase (PAH), rendering it nonfunctional.

name: ocular hypertension
descr: An eye disease that is characterized by elevated intraocular pressure in the absence of optic nerve damage or visual field loss.

name: priapism
descr: A peripheral vascular disease characterized by blood trapped in the penis that is unable to drain.

name: cleft lip
descr: An orofacial cleft that is characterized by a congenital defect in the upper lip where the maxillary prominence fails to merge with the merged medial nasal prominences.

name: language disorder
descr: A communication disorder that involves the processing of linguistic information.

name: orbital disease
descr: An adnexa disease that is located_in the eye socket.

name: splenic tuberculosis
descr: An abdominal tuberculosis that results_in formation of granulomas or abscesses located_in spleen.

name: monieziasis
descr: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves zoonotic infection caused by Moniezia expansa, the common tapeworm of sheep.

name: chronic ethmoiditis
descr: A ethmoid sinusitis which lasts for 12 weeks or more.

name: lymphangitis
descr: A lymphatic system disease that is characterized by inflammation of the lymphatic channels which occurs as a result of infection at a site distal to the channel. It is caused by Streptococcus pyogenes (Group A strep) or Staphylococcus aureus. Lymphangitis is also sometimes called blood poisoning.

name: viral infectious disease
descr: A disease by infectious agent that results in infection, has_material_basis_in Viruses.

name: diabetes mellitus
descr: A glucose metabolism disease characterized  by chronic hyperglycaemia with disturbances of carbohydrate, fat and protein metabolism resulting from defects in insulin secretion, insulin action, or both.

name: type 2 diabetes mellitus
descr: A diabetes mellitus that involves high blood glucose resulting from cells fail to use insulin properly.

name: brain disease
descr: A central nervous system disease that is located_in the brain.

name: intrinsic asthma
descr: An asthma that is triggered by factors not related to allergies such as anxiety, stress, exercise, cold air, dry air, hyperventilation, smoke, viruses, chemical irritants, autonomic imbalance, hormonal deficiencies and psychogenic influences. It is characterized by airway obstruction and inflammation that is at least partially reversible with medication. The symptoms include coughing, wheezing, shortness of breath or rapid breathing, and chest tightness.

name: status asthmaticus
descr: An asthma that is a life threatening condition with progressive respiratory failure, which does not respond to standard treatment.

name: exophthalmos
descr: An eye disease that is characterized by a bulging of the eye anteriorly out of the orbit.

name: Fuchs' heterochromic uveitis
descr: A syndrome that is a chronic unilateral (or rarely bilateral) iridocyclitis appearing with the triad of heterochromia, predisposition to cataracts and glaucoma, and keratitic percipitates on the posterior corneal surface.

name: tracheitis
descr: A tracheal disease which involves bacterial infection of the trachea often caused by Staphylococcus aureus and streptococci that follows a recent viral upper respiratory infection. The symptoms include barking croup cough, loud squeaking noise while breathing, scratchy feeling in the throat, high fever, and production of large amounts of pus-filled secretions.

name: croup
descr: A respiratory system infectious disease that involves inflammation, edema, and subsequent obstruction of the larynx, trachea, and bronchi. The disease is caused by viruses, bacteria, allergies and inhaled irritants. It is marked by episodes of difficult breathing and hoarse metallic cough in infants and young children. Croup is caused by parainfluenza virus (types 1 and 2), Influenza A and B viruses, Measles virus, adenovirus, respiratory syncytial virus, Staphylococcus and Streptococcus.

name: acute laryngitis
descr: A laryngitis which lasts less than a few days.

name: epiglottitis
descr: An upper respiratory tract disease which involves inflammation of the epiglottis due to infection. Haemophilus influenzae type B is the most common bacterial causative agent, although some cases are attributable to Streptococcus pneumoniae or Streptococcus pyogenes. The infection can cause the epiglottis to either obstruct or completely close off the windpipe. Epiglottitis typically affects children, and is associated with fever, difficulty in swallowing, drooling, hoarseness of voice, and stridor.

name: hypopituitarism
descr: A pituitary gland disease characterized by the decreased secretion of one or more of the eight hormones normally produced by the pituitary gland.

name: allergic asthma
descr: An asthma that is characterized by symptoms that are triggered by an allergic reaction caused by inhaled allergens such as dust mite allergen, pet dander, pollen and mold. Allergic asthma is airway obstruction and inflammation that is partially reversible with medication. The disease has_symptom coughing, has_symptom wheezing, has_symptom shortness of breath or has_symptom rapid breathing, and has_symptom chest tightness.

name: blepharitis
descr: An eyelid disease that is characterized by often chronic inflammation of the eyelid, generally the part where eyelashes grow.

name: intracranial hypertension
descr: A brain disease that is characterized by high pressure inside the skull, the brain tissue and cerebrospinal fluid, has_symptom headache, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom altered mental status, has_symptom papilledema.

name: cervical Mullerian papilloma
descr: A cervical benign neoplasm that is a polypoid lesion of the superficial cervix or vagina of young girls to adult women and is characterized by papillary stalks covered by mucinous epithelium with focal squamous metaplasia, highly cellular fibrous tissue, no atypia, and minimal mitotic activity.

name: cervix squamous papilloma
descr: A cervical benign neoplasm that is a polypoid lesion characterized by a single papillary frond with a central fibrovascular core and mature squamous epithelium.

name: cholangitis
descr: A bile duct disease that is an inflammation of the bile duct.

name: fatty liver disease
descr: A lipid storage disease characterized by the accumulation of large vacuoles of triglyceride fat in liver cells via the process of steatosis.

name: lipid storage disease
descr: A lysosomal storage disease that involves the accumulation of harmful amounts of lipids (fats) in some of the body's cells and tissues.

name: dientamoebiasis
descr: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection of the large intestine by a protozoan parasite Dientamoeba fragilis. The symptoms include diarrhea, stomach pain and cramping, loss of appetite and weight, nausea, and fatigue.

name: uterine corpus cancer
descr: A uterine cancer that is located_in the uterine corpus.

name: cholesteatoma of external ear
descr: A cholesteatoma which involves invasion of the squamous tissue into a localized area of bony erosion of the ear canal. It may develop spontaneously or as a consequence of infection, trauma or surgery.

name: otitis externa
descr: An external ear disease that involves inflammation of the outer ear and ear canal. It can be caused by active bacterial or fungal infections.

name: bacterial meningitis
descr: A meningitis that has_material_basis_in a bacterial infection.

name: meningitis
descr: A central nervous system disease that is characterized by an inflammation of the pia-arachnoid meninges. It can be caused by growth of bacteria, fungi, or parasites within the subarachnoid space or by the growth of bacteria or viruses within the meningeal or ependymal cells.

name: pulmonary embolism
descr: An artery disease characterized by a blockage of the main artery of the lung or one of its branches by a substance that has travelled from elsewhere in the body, e.g. a blood clot.

name: postpartum depression
descr: An endogenous depression that involves intense, sustained and sometimes disabling depression experienced by women after giving birth.

name: Meckel's diverticulum
descr: A physical disorder that is characterized by a congenital abnormality characterized by the outpouching or sac formation in the ileum.

name: pulmonary eosinophilia
descr: A hypereosinophilic syndrome characterized by the accumulation of eosinophils in the lungs.

name: leukocyte disease
descr: A hematopoietic system disease that is located_in white blood cells.

name: chronic eosinophilic pneumonia
descr: An eosinophilic pneumonia which slowly progresses over weeks to months. Life-threatening shortness of breath can develop if the condition is not treated. Individuals are often diagnosed with asthma before the advent of this disease.

name: Loeffler syndrome
descr: An eosinophilic pneumonia described as a form of pulmonary eosinophilia characterized as a mild pneumonitis marked by transitory pulmonary infiltration and eosinophilia and usually considered to be an allergic reaction. It can occur in response to a parasitic infection.

name: benign mammary dysplasia
descr: A breast benign neoplasm that encompasses a range of conditions in which there is marked change in the breast tissue.

name: cannabis abuse
descr: A substance abuse that involves the recurring use of cannabis despite negative consequences.

name: acute ethmoiditis
descr: A ethmoid sinusitis which lasts for less than 4 weeks.

name: ethmoid sinusitis
descr: A sinusitis which involves infection of ethmoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind and between the eyes, tearing, and headache over the forehead.

name: latent syphilis
descr: A syphilis that is characterized as having serologic proof of infection without signs or symptoms of disease.

name: tuberculous pneumothorax
descr: A pneumothorax in which air enters into the pleural cavity.

name: Lassa fever
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection, has_material_basis_in Lassa virus, which is transmitted_by multimammate rat of the genus Mastomys. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom retrosternal pain, has_symptom sore throat, has_symptom back pain, has_symptom cough, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom conjunctivitis, has_symptom facial swelling, has_symptom proteinuria (protein in the urine), and has_symptom mucosal bleeding.

name: multiple myeloma
descr: A myeloid neoplasm that is located in the plasma cells in bone marrow.

name: smoldering myeloma
descr: A multiple myeloma that is a slow growing type of myeloma in which abnormal plasma cells results_in too much of a single type of monoclonal antibody.

name: adrenal gland disease
descr: An endocrine system disease that is located_in the adrenal gland.

name: primary ciliary dyskinesia
descr: A ciliopathy that is characterized by impaired function of the cilia lining the respiratory tract (lower and upper, sinuses, Eustachian tube, middle ear) and fallopian tube.

name: bronchiectasis
descr: A bronchial disease that is a chronic inflammatory condition of one or more bronchi or bronchioles marked by dilatation and loss of elasticity of the walls resulting from damage to the airway wall leading to the formation of small sacs on the bronchial wall and impairment of cilia mobility in the lung. Inflammation of the bronchial wall increases mucus secretion which serves as a breeding ground for bacteria. Bronchiectasis is caused by repeated respiratory infections, immune deficiency disorders, hereditary disorders (cystic fibrosis or primary ciliary dyskinesia), mechanical factors (inhaled object or a lung tumor) or inhaling toxic substances.

name: neonatal candidiasis
descr: A candidiasis that involves fungal infection in neonates caused by Candida species. Low birthweight and age, prolonged intravascular catheterization and the use of antibiotic drugs are the principle predisposing conditions for systemic candidiasis in neonates.

name: Venezuelan equine encephalitis
descr: A viral infectious disease that results_in inflammation located_in brain of horses and humans, has_material_basis_in Venezuelan equine encephalitis virus, which is transmitted_by Culex mosquitoes. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom severe headache, has_symptom photophobia, and has_symptom myalgia in the legs and lumbosacral region.

name: encephalitis
descr: A brain disease that is characterized as an acute inflammation of the brain with flu-like symptoms.

name: lower urinary tract calculus
descr: A urinary system disease that is located_in the lower urinary tract and is characterized by the formation of a stone.

name: Krukenberg carcinoma
descr: An ovary epithelial cancer that is a metastatic signet-ring cell carcinoma, which spreads to the ovary from gastric tissue.

name: fasciitis
descr: A connective tissue disease characterized by inflammation located_in the fascia.

name: staphyloenterotoxemia
descr: A primary bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection located_in intestine caused by eating food contaminated with enterotoxins produced by bacteria, has_material_basis_in Staphylococcus aureus. The infection has_symptom diarrhea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom cramps, and has_symptom weakness.

name: vesicoureteral reflux
descr: A ureteral disease characterized by backward flow of urine from the urinary bladder into the ureter.

name: episodic ataxia
descr: A hereditary ataxia characterized by sporadic bouts of ataxia with or without continuous muscle movement.

name: sarcocystosis
descr: A coccidiosis that involves infection of the intestine and muscles of humans and animals caused by an intracellular protozoan parasite of genus Sarcocystis. The symptoms include mild fever, diarrhea, chills, vomiting, muscle swelling, erythema, muscle tenderness,cough, arthralgia, transient pruritic rashes, headache, malaise and lymphadenopathy.

name: babesiosis
descr: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that has_symptom mild fevers and has_symptom anemia described as malaria-like symptoms caused by a protozoan of genus Babesia, which reproduce in red blood cells and cause hemolytic anemia. They are transmitted by Ixodid ticks or by blood transfusion. Babesiosis is a zoonotic disease.

name: congenital nystagmus
descr: A pathologic nystagmus, present at birth, characterized by involuntary, rhythmic eye movements; oscillations are usually horizontal in direction.

name: aphthous stomatitis
descr: A stomatitis characterized by the repeated formation of benign and non-contagious mouth ulcers.

name: placental abruption
descr: A placenta disease that is characterized by separation of the placental lining from the uterus of the mother.

name: senile cataract
descr: A cataract that is characterized by thickening and loss of transparency of the lens with age progression, caused by a multifactorial etiology related to aging.

name: cervical incompetence
descr: A cervix disease that is characterized by the beginning of dilation and effacement of a pregnant woman's cervix before her pregnancy has reached term.

name: yellow fever
descr: A viral infectious disease that results in infection, has_material_basis_in Yellow fever virus, which is transmitted by Aedes, transmitted by Haemagogus, or transmitted by Sabethes species of mosquitoes. The infection has symptom fever, has symptom muscle pain, has symptom backache, has symptom headache, has symptom shivers, has symptom loss of appetite, has symptom jaundice, and has symptom bleeding from the mouth, nose, eyes or stomach leading to vomitus containing blood.

name: toxic myocarditis
descr: An acute myocarditis that is characterized by an underlying toxin insult to the myocardium that induces acute inflammation.

name: ophthalmia neonatorum
descr: A bacterial conjuctivitis that is characterized by pain and tenderness in the eyeball and conjuctival discharge.

name: vitreous disease
descr: An eye and adnexa disease that is located in the vitreous of the eye.

name: vitreous abscess
descr: A vitreous disease that is characterized by an abscess located_in the vitreous of the eye.

name: renal tuberculosis
descr: An urogenital tuberculosis that results_in formation of granulomas located_in kidney.

name: acute allergic mucoid otitis media
descr: A blue drum syndrome caused by an allergen.

name: blue drum syndrome
descr: A acute transudative otitis media involving thick, viscid and mucuslike fluid effusion due to which the drum appears blue in color.

name: eustachian tube disease
descr: A non-suppurative otitis media and eustachian tube disorder in which the tube is either too narrow or too wide. It can also be cuased by nasal inflammation which leads to inflammatory swelling and obstruction of the eustachian tube, which, in turn, leads to increased negative pressure in the middle ear and improper ventilation.

name: upper respiratory tract disease
descr: A respiratory system disease which involves the upper respiratory tract.

name: pelvic varices
descr: A varicose veins that is located_in the pelvis.

name: type 1 diabetes mellitus
descr: A diabetes mellitus that results from the body's failure to produce insulin and has_material_basis_in autoimmune destruction of insulin-producing beta cells of the pancreas.

name: hemorrhoid
descr: A pelvic varix disease characterized by swollen, inflamed veins around the anus or lower rectum.

name: emphysematous cholecystitis
descr: Emphysematous cholecystitis is a bacterial infectious disease consisting of an inflammation of the gallbladder characterized by air-filled expansions in interstitial or subcutaneous tissues.

name: female breast upper-outer quadrant cancer
descr: A female breast cancer that is located_in the upper-outer quadrant of the breast.

name: irritable bowel syndrome
descr: A syndrome that is a functional bowel disorder characterized by chronic abdominal pain, discomfort, bloating, and alteration of bowel habits in the absence of any detectable organic cause.

name: trichinosis
descr: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of animals and humans by Trichinella spiralis, Trichinella nativa or Trichinella britovi. Intestinal invasion causes diarrhea, abdominal pain and vomiting. Larval migration into muscle tissues can cause periorbital and facial edema, conjunctivitis, fever, myalgias, splinter hemorrhages, rashes, and blood eosinophilia. Myocarditis, central nervous system involvement, and pneumonitis can also occur.

name: bulbar polio
descr: A paralytic poliomyelitis that results in destruction located in motor neurons of brainstem, has_material_basis_in Human poliovirus 1, has_material_basis_in Human poliovirus 2, or has_material_basis_in Human poliovirus 3, which are transmitted by ingestion of food or water contaminated with feces, or transmitted by direct contact with the oral secretions. The infection has symptom difficulty breathing, has symptom difficulty speaking, has symptom difficulty swallowing, and has symptom difficulty chewing.

name: toxocariasis
descr: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves zoonotic infection of humans by the larvae of Toxocara canis or Toxocara cati. The larvae invade multiple tissues like liver, heart, lungs, brain, muscle and eyes causing various symptoms including fever, anorexia, weight loss, cough, wheezing, rashes, hepatosplenomegaly, hypereosinophilia and ophthalmologic lesions.

name: tuberculous peritonitis
descr: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that results_in inflammation located_in peritoneum, which results in formation of tubercles. The infection has_symptom abdominal discomfort, has_symptom pain, has_symptom distention from gas or fluid, has_symptom digestive disturbances and has_symptom emaciation.

name: Goodpasture syndrome
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease that is characterized by antibody attack of the basement membrane in lungs and kidneys, leading to bleeding from the lungs and kidney failure.

name: hypersensitivity vasculitis
descr: A hypersensitivity reaction type III disease that is characterized by inflammation and injury to blood vessels and has_symptom purpura, telangiectasia, blistering, urticaria, and ulcers.

name: polyarteritis nodosa
descr: A vasculitis that is characterized by necrotizing inflammation of medium or small arteries.

name: neonatal abstinence syndrome
descr: A withdrawal disorder that is characterized by a group of problems that occur in a newborn who was exposed to addictive illegal or prescription drugs while in the mother's womb or postnatally following the discontinuance of drug treatment.

name: esotropia
descr: A strabismus that is characterized the eye which turns inward toward the nose.

name: Meniere's disease
descr: A vestibular disease characterized by vertigo, low-pitched tinnitus and hearing loss.

name: congenital syphilis
descr: A syphilis that results_in a multisystem infection in the fetus via the placenta.

name: interstitial keratitis
descr: A connective tissue disease characterized by corneal scarring that develops from non-suppurative inflammation located_in the corneal stroma, has_symptom visual acuity loss, has_symptom pain, and has_symptom lacrimation.

name: alopecia areata
descr: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease resulting in the loss of hair on the scalp and elsewhere on the body initially causing bald spots.

name: miliary tuberculosis
descr: An extrapulmonary tuberculosis that results in formation of tiny lesions in all the organs.

name: alopecia
descr: A hypotrichosis that is characterized by a loss of hair from the head or body.

name: galactosemia
descr: A carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves a defect in galactose metabolism resulting in toxic levels of galactose 1-phosphate in various tissues.

name: mitral valve prolapse
descr: A mitral valve disease where one or both of the cusps of the mitral valve bulge or collapse backward in the left atrium during systole.

name: cardiovascular syphilis
descr: A tertiary syphilis that is manifested as aneurysm formation in the ascending aorta, caused by chronic inflammatory destruction of the vasa vasorum, insufficiency of the aortic valve, or narrowing of the coronary arteries.

name: Becker muscular dystrophy
descr: A muscular dystrophy that involves slowly worsening muscle weakness of the legs and pelvis, and has_material_basis in X-linked recessive inheritance of mutation in the dystrophin gene on chromosome Xp21.

name: muscular dystrophy
descr: A myopathy is characterized by progressive skeletal muscle weakness degeneration.

name: congenital heart block
descr: An atrioventricular block characterized by the presence of conduction system disease of any form, which is diagnosed on or before 28 days of life.

name: meibomian cyst
descr: A blepharitis that is characterized as a cyst in the eyelid that is caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland, usually on the upper eyelid.

name: hordeolum
descr: Hordeolum is a sequelae of infectious and parasitic disease consisting of an infection of the sebaceous glands at the base of the eyelashes. Styes are generally caused by a Staphylococcus aureus bacterial infection.

name: central corneal ulcer
descr: A corneal ulcer that is characterized by ulceration and opacification of the central cornea and is caused by minor trauma and subsequent infection by bacterial or mycotic organisms.

name: Omsk hemorrhagic fever
descr: A viral infectious disease that is a hemorrhagic fever, has_material_basis_in Omsk hemorrhagic fever virus, which is transmitted_by Dermacentor and transmitted_by Ixodes species of ticks. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom headache, has_symptom pain in lower and upper extremities, has_symptom stiff neck, has_symptom papulovesicular rash on the soft palate, has_symptom cervical lymphadenopathy, has_symptom conjunctival suffusion, has_symptom blood in the urine, and has_symptom blood in the sputum.

name: developmental coordination disorder
descr: A specific developmental disorder that involves disordered motor skills where coordinated muscle movement is impaired.

name: Waterhouse-Friderichsen syndrome
descr: An adrenal gland disease that is characterized by failure of the adrenal gland due to bleeding into the gland.

name: chronic inflammation of lacrimal passage
descr: A lacrimal apparatus disease that is characterized by longstanding inflammation of the lacrimal passage, and has_symptom pain, increased or decreased tearing, and swelling between the eye and nose.

name: dacryocystitis
descr: An acute inflammation of lacrimal passage that is characterized by inflammation of the lacrimal sac, has_symptom conjunctivitis and has_symptom purulent discharge.

name: acute lymphocytic leukemia
descr: A lymphoblastic leukemia that is characterized by over production of lymphoblasts.

name: hypoplastic left heart syndrome
descr: A congenital heart disease characterized by abnormal development of the left-sided structures of the heart.

name: periostitis
descr: A connective tissue disease characterized by inflammation located_in the periosteum of the bone.

name: hemometra
descr: A uterine disease that is characterized by the presence of blood in the uterine cavity.

name: toxoplasmosis
descr: A coccidiosis that has_material_basis_in protozoan Toxoplasma gondii. The parasite effects most genera of warm-blooded animals, including humans, but the primary host is the felid (cat) family. Animals are infected by eating infected meat, by ingestion of feces of a cat that has itself recently been infected, or transmission_by mother to fetus. The symptoms include bilateral, nontender cervical or axillary lymphadenopathy, fever, malaise, myalgia, hepatosplenomegaly, anemia and leukopenia.

name: uterine inversion
descr: A uterine disease that is characterized by the uterine cavity turning inside out as a complication of childbirth.

name: obesity
descr: An overnutrition that is characterized by excess body fat, traditionally defined as an elevated ratio of weight to height (specifically 30 kilograms per meter squared), has_material_basis_in a multifactorial etiology related to excess nutrition intake, decreased caloric utilization, and genetic susceptibility, and possibly medications and certain disorders of metabolism, endocrine function, and mental illness.

name: hypervitaminosis D
descr: An overnutrition that is characterized by elevated vitamin D, which can subsequently cause high levels of calcium, has_symptom myalgia, fatigue, irritability, nausea, dehydration, polyuria, and nephrocalcinosis, and possibly has_material_basis_in excess intake of vitamin D.

name: hypervitaminosis A
descr: An overnutrition that is characterized by excess vitamin A, has_symptom hepatomegaly, anorexia, fever, alopecia, and arthralgia, and has_material_basis_in excessive intake of vitaimin A, and/or derangement of vitamin A metabolism.

name: substance dependence
descr: A substance-related disorder that involves the continued use of alcohol or other drugs despite problems related to use of the substance.

name: drug dependence
descr: A substance dependence that involves the continued use of drugs despite problems related to use of the substance.

name: cocaine dependence
descr: A drug dependence that is a psychological dependency on the regular use of cocaine.

name: heroin dependence
descr: An opiate dependence that involves the continued use of heroin despite problems related to use of the substance.

name: hallucinogen dependence
descr: A drug dependence that involves the continued use of hallucinogenic drugs despite problems related to use of the substance.

name: tertiary neurosyphilis
descr: A tertiary syphilis that results in infection located in brain or located in spinal cord.

name: hypoglycemia
descr: A glucose metabolism disease that is characterized by abnormally low levels of blood glucose.
